title: cream cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, half and half and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in other ingredients.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Mix gelatin in water.
Fold in strawberries with juice.
Drain pineapple.
Mix together pineapple, bananas and nuts well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 12 x 8-inch dish and refrigerate until firm. Spread sour cream over jelled mixture.
Spoon remainder of mixture on top.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: baked onion soup
directions: Pour onion soup into two 8 ounce ramekins.
Float a croutet on top covered with Swiss cheese in each.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese and top with a pat of butter.
Microwave one at a time on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese bubbles around edges.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Marinate vermicelli overnight in Accent, lemon juice and oil. Next day, add celery, onions, peppers, pimento and black olives. Toss with mayonnaise and salt.

title: escalloped baked corn
directions: Mix eggs, corn, salt and sugar.
Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Mix with corn.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Corn is never watery.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt and mix caramel and milk together.
Spread over the baked layer.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped pecans.
Cover with remaining cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with taco chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add bananas and 2 beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in large greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine
jello,
7-Up
or Sprite, sugar, cornstarch and red food
coloring.
Boil until thick.	Place berries in cool pie crust.
Pour hot mixture over berries and chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: parsley gurken's
directions: Slice cucumber 1/4-inch thick.
Put in bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 8 hours.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water, pickling spice, turmeric and lemon peel in saucepan.
Boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Drain cucumbers.
Return to bowl.
Stir in parsley.
Pour hot liquid mixture over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 days, stirring once a day.
Refrigerate pickles in covered glass containers for up to 2 months.

title: deli-in-a-skillet
directions: Mix corned beef, sauerkraut and water in a large skillet. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Pour dressing over rice and top with cheese.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Kielbasa, knockwurst or similar meat may be substituted for the corned beef.

title: granola
directions: Mix together in large pan.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
The less dry, the more chewy.

title: fancy sauerkraut salad
directions: Stir in sugar with sauerkraut.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover bowl tightly.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat just until moistened. Spoon into a greased 8 inch square baking dish.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Clean and pare broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces. Add onion; in bowl, pour boiling water over raisins, let stand 5 minutes.
Mix salad dressing with sugar or honey, pour over prepared vegetables.
Add raisins and bacon.
Mix lightly. Refrigerate until serving.

title: peasant bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
In a large bowl, combine flour, salt and sugar.
Add yeast mixture and remaining water; stir until combined.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Stir dough down.
Divide in half.
Place each half in a greased 1-quart round casserole or ovenproof bowl. Brush tops with butter; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: peach pickles
directions: Mix liquid ingredients with spice and pour over peaches.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine with crushed pretzels. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and let cool.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Then mix in vanilla and one cup of flour at a time.
Batter will be thick (you may have to wet your fingers to spread it in the pan).
Spread 1/2 the batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan, then pour pie filling over that.
Spoon rest of batter on top to almost cover it.
(Some of the filling will show through.)
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
(I greased my baking dish also.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir well.
Add 1 pound of nuts; pour on greased cake sheet; when cool, cut into squares.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add salt and baking powder, then sift again.
Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugar together until the mixture is light and fluffy. Add the eggs.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk, beating until smooth. Fold in raisins and add vanilla to blend.
Drop by teaspoon on a lightly greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Remove 3/4 cup for topping. Add 2 cups sour milk with 1 tsp. baking soda stirred in to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice to taste.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° until done approximately 40 - 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.	Store in refrigerator.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese, sugar, and milk and fold into Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture over the cake which has been broken into small pieces.
Use a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish or 2 smaller dishes.
Put the amount of cherry pie filling on top that you like.
I don't use the whole can.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Lightly brown chops slowly in 1 tablespoon oil, then add 1/4-inch slice of a large onion, 1/4-inch slice bell pepper on each chop.
Then pour 1 can tomato soup over chops.
Cover skillet and cook on low heat for perhaps 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Baste several times as they cook.
Serve with rice.
A delicious gravy is made.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Good with butter brickle or butter pecan ice cream.

title: grilled redfish
directions: Prepare charcoal fire with dried mesquite added.
Season fillets.
Squeeze lime juice into melted margarine or butter.
Cook fillets skin and scale side down directly over hot fire with grill 10 to 12-inches from fire for 15 to 20 minutes or until done, basting continuously with lime and margarine or butter mixture.
To remove from grill, use spatula to scoop meat from skin, leaving skin on grill.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook pork roast in crock-pot overnight on low.
The next morning take the bone out and shred the pork.
Add equal amounts of hot and mild barbecue sauce and mix.
Use the Louisiana hot sauce to make it as hot as you want.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: apple cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl, except apples and sugar and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth and pour half of mixture into Bundt cake pan.
Pare and core apples; slice very thin.
Cover batter with half of the apple slices and sugar and cinnamon. Cover with rest of batter.
Arrange remaining apple slices on top and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chili
directions: Brown the hamburger, butter, onion and salt.
Cut and cook the celery, water and salt for 15 minutes.
Mix the above ingredients with the remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine; add brown sugar and hot water and mix well. Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts and mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
This recipe makes 2 dozen bars.

title: white bread(2 loaves)
directions: Mix water, sugar, salt and oil in saucepan.
Put in yeast. Stir a couple of times and let stand until yeast forms little spots of rising.
Put sifted flour in large bowl, then put in other ingredients.
Knead well and let rise a couple of hours or until double.
Put into loaves or rolls and let rise again.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes, at 350°.
More or less as needed.

title: greek tomato salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer tomatoes, onions and olives. Sprinkle with cheese and oregano.
Combine oil and vinegar.
Pour over tomato mixture.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and half of the flour.
Mix by hand.
Add egg, butter and rest of flour.
Cover and let rise.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Do not knead. Roll out as for jelly roll.
Brush with margarine (about 1/4 cup). Generously sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll and slice. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: nut fingers
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt together either with hands or mixer.
Beat eggs and vanilla in cup with fork, then add to batter and mix.
Mix yeast and cold milk, then add to batter.
Mix until the dough comes off your hands and bowl.
Separate dough into sizes about as big as a grapefruit.
Put in bowl and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix #1:
Mix the cream cheese, margarine, sugar and Cool Whip in a large bowl.

title: country fried steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size.
Season with salt and pepper. Beat steaks on both sides.
Dredge with flour and brown in hot shortening.
Add onions and stir in 2 tablespoons flour into drippings.
Brown, if desired.
Add water, cover and simmer 2 hours or until tender.

title: beef vegetable bake
directions: Cook meat; add tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, combine potatoes, green pepper, onion, celery and meat mixture.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar adding eggs one at a time and beating after each addition.
Add honey to sweet milk.
Add salt, baking powder and spices to sifted flour and sift again.
Dust fruit and nuts with a little of the flour mixture.
Mix liquid and dry ingredients alternately to the egg mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into greased tube or loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour or until toothpick is clean after testing.
Frost as desired.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken with sour cream, grated cheese and salt.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; roll up and arrange side by side, seam side down, in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour salsa over enchiladas, covering each one completely.
Bake at 250° until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Makes 15 enchiladas.

title: cottage cheese salmon loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Can be served plain or with your favorite fish or cheese sauce.
This loaf is nice and moist.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together oil, garlic powder, dill weed and dressing.
In a brown paper bag, place several layers of paper towels.
Place 1/2 of crackers on towels and drizzle 1/2 oil mixture over crackers. Cover with another layer of towels and add remaining crackers and drizzle remaining oil mixture over top.
Cover with more paper towels.
Leave bag closed for 30 minutes, shaking bag every 10 minutes.
Remove crackers and store in tight container.

title: polynesian sweet and sour sauce(walt disney world)
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water, the vinegar, sugar and food coloring, if desired.	Bring to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water and stir into vinegar mixture, using a whisk.
Cook and stir five minutes.
Add green pepper, onion and pineapple.	Serve on shrimp, chicken or pork.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding pecans last. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour or until edges are firm at 300°.

title: chocolate trifle with angel food cake
directions: Cook pudding following package directions.
Place thin layer of pudding in bottom of trifle dish.
Make a layer of angel food cake.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle half of the pecans over the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and garnish with pecans. Enjoy!
This recipe comes from Laura Smith.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine syrup and sugar and bring to a boil.
As soon as it reaches a good boil, remove.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in vanilla and cereal.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook, stirring constantly, to hard crack stage, 300°.
Remove from heat and add butter and soda.
Stir and then pour onto oiled pan.

title: tzatziki(cucumber yogurt dip)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla, then add flour and knead to make a soft dough.
Let rise and punch down.
Let rise before baking on a cookie sheet (greased).
Shape as a loaf.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: granita di caffe
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil for several minutes; pour Espresso into the mixture in pan.
Dissolve cocoa powder in it and remove pan from the heat.
Let cool completely.
Pour mixture into a bowl and freeze until solid.
Transfer to a blender and blend until slushy. Pour into 6 cappuccino cups or small wine glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add crumbs.
Add a layer of coconut, then add a layer of chocolate chips.
Pour layer of milk, then nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together.
Add water and grated rind.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir hot mixture into egg yolks which have been mixed with lemon juice.
Strain into baked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and peanut butter into a crumb mixture.
Place crumb mixture on bottom of baked pie crust (saving some for top of pie).
Then mix the chocolate pudding as directed on the box for a pie and put on top of the crumb mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Shake beef pieces in bag with flour.
Brown in butter or a little oil.
Add water to cover 2 to 3 inches.
Add bay leaf, salt, pepper and onion.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add red wine; cook 1/2 hour more.
Thicken if necessary.
Serve over boiled whole potatoes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, butter and pecans in bowl; mix well. Fold whipped cream gently into mixture.
Layer half the vanilla wafer crumbs, all the pineapple mixture and remaining crumbs in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill overnight.

title: meatballs
directions: Brown sliced onion.
Mix soup, 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and sugar.
Add to onions, simmer while making meatballs.
Mix egg, hamburger, bread crumbs, 1/3 cup water, salt and poultry seasoning.
Make into small balls.
Add one at a time to sauce. Simmer 1 to 2 hours, stirring gently, occasionally.
Sauce will thicken as it cooks.
I usually prepare three times the recipe. It seems to taste better as it is heated again.
It makes great leftovers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix gently all ingredients, except catsup.
Shape into a loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven. Spoon catsup on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: lena's apple cake
directions: Mix bowl No. 1 ingredients.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In 6-quart pot, combine all ingredients and place over medium heat.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the hamburger and cut up bacon. Add the onion and cook slightly. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.

title: yum-yum chicken
directions: Boil chicken in 2 quarts water with seasonings to taste. Remove chicken and reserve 1 cup broth.
Bone chicken, cut into bite size pieces and place in 9x13x2-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream; spoon over chicken.
Top with stuffing mix. Melt margarine in broth and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broiled crab legs
directions: Thaw crab legs.
Combine 1/4 cup of butter with remaining ingredients and blend
well.
Place
crab
legs on broiler rack and brush with butter
sauce.
Broil
to 5 inches from heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Brush once with sauce and serve with additional butter if desired.	Makes 2 main dish servings.

title: nectar cake
directions: Mix well and bake in Bundt baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cook approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
No frosting needed.
If you want a frosting, make a glaze.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Put sugar, molasses, butter, soda, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and butter in bowl and dissolve 2 teaspoons soda in 1 cup boiling water.
Hold soda water over bowl as it foams over cup.
Beat together. When well beaten, add 2 well beaten eggs the last thing before baking.
Bake in an oblong pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or as desired.

title: baked caramel custard
directions: To caramelize dish, choose a heatproof 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Place sugar and water into dish and heat on High setting for 3 to 4 minutes until sugar melts and starts to turn brown.
Watch carefully and turn dish to coat evenly.
Let caramel coating cool before pouring in the custard.
To make custard, beat remaining ingredients together and pour into caramelized dish.
Set into larger dish containing water to reach 1-inch up the side. Cook on Medium-high setting for 15 to 18 minutes until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Blend thoroughly. Store in tightly capped bottle in refrigerator.
Serve over ice.

title: twila's pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add syrup and white sugar to mixture.
Place pecans in bottom of the pie shell and add filling on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or longer as necessary for filling to set.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage (drain).
Return to pan; add the cream cheese. Cook on low until cream cheese is melted.
Then add the Cheddar cheese while this is melting.
Put 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of casserole dish.
When meat is ready, put it on top of the rolls. Top with other package rolls.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt; stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each addition.
Stir in coconut and oats.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all, except coconut, in blender.
Stir in coconut.
Pour in greased and floured large pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Makes its own crust.)
Without cream cheese, it's like coconut custard pie.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares of desired size.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Make sauce of Coca-Cola, catsup and mustard.
Place chicken in heavy saucepan. Pour sauce over chicken and let boil.
Then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna(microwave)
directions: Crumble meat into strainer and put in container to catch grease.
Cover and microwave on High, 3 to 4 minutes.
In 1-quart bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, Ricotta or cottage cheese, oregano, salt and pepper plus cooked meat; mix well.

title: casserola la paloma
directions: Blend soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Spread into 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Mix melted margarine, parsley and cornflake crumbs and top casserole. Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: ziti with chicken and peppers
directions: Heat oil in a heavy, 3-quart saucepan or skillet.
Add green pepper and onion and saute over medium heat for 5 minutes until barely tender.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring, until mushrooms wilt, about 5 minutes longer.
Add chicken and cook, stirring, until chicken turns white.
Stir in tomatoes, broth and tomato paste.
Simmer for two minutes, then add oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Have ziti ready and add to mixture.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and onion until tender.
Cool.
Skin, bone and chop chicken.
Place chicken on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drain vegetables and pour on top of chicken.
Mix broth and soup.
Pour over vegetables.
Combine buttermilk, flour and margarine.
Spoon over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower together in boiling water just until tender; drain.
Stir chicken soup, cheese spread and half of the onion into the drained vegetables.
Turn vegetables mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: thailand chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and brown lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Simmer 15 minutes and serve over rice.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce and cauliflower into bite size pieces. Slice onion and crumble bacon.

title: 1-2-3 congealed salad(christmas salad)
directions: Mix lime jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add canned pears and congeal.
(Pear liquid may be used in place of water.)
Mix lemon jello with 1 cup hot water, cream cheese and whipping cream.
When mixed and cooled, pour on top of lime jello.
(Turn a spoon over and pour lime jello to keep from melting in one place.)
Mix strawberry jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water and pineapple.
Let cool and pour over the lemon mixture.

title: hearty breakfast
directions: Place 6 slices of buttered bread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay a slice of cheese on each slice of bread.
Beat together the following and pour over the bread and cheese: eggs, milk, salt, mustard and onion.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
In the morning, fry bacon or sausage.
Crumble and spread over the bread and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Cook beef in oil until red disappears.
Add onion and celery. Cook until onion is soft.
Add catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce and other seasonings.
Mix well.
Stir in macaroni.
Cover. Simmer about 25 minutes.
Fold in cheese just before serving. Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.
Serve hot from skillet.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Heat oil in a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic.
Cook until light brown.
Add basil, oregano, parsley, crushed red pepper and reserved clam liquid. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes.
Add clams; cook, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
While clam sauce is simmering, cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
Serve clam sauce over hot spaghetti. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixer bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar. Continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand stir in flour, frosting mix and nuts until well blended.
Pour batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool for 2 hours in pan.

title: pineapple angel pie
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl until well blended. Do not whip or beat.
Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: niguel children center's kool-aid play dough
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in boiling water.
Add other ingredients. Mix together.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding grapes and mayonnaise last. Serve on plate of shredded lettuce.
Garnish with pineapple chunks.

title: summer salad
directions: After beef has been browned and drained, add beans (drained) and onions.
After mixture has cooled about 15 minutes, add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Mix well in a very large bowl. Right before time to serve, add dressing and Fritos and mix well again.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine over hot (not boiling) water, semi-sweet chocolate morsels and sweetened condensed milk.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla extract.
Spread into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: sole with rosemary
directions: Place fish in baking dish so they fit snugly.
Prepare a mixture of olive oil, lemon juice, wine, parsley and rosemary.
Mix all ingredients and pour over fish.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until fish barely begins to flake.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: moose stew
directions: Sear meat in a stew pot; add soups and water sufficient to cover veggies.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Phil often adds frozen peas or green limas (or anything else that strikes his fancy).

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix carrots with bread crumbs, cream, celery, parsley, onion, eggs and melted butter and put in a ring mold.
Set mold in water and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Unmold onto serving plate and fill the center of the mold with creamed peas or peas with cheese sauce.

title: applesauce walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round cake pans.
Put dry cake mix, butter, eggs, applesauce and cinnamon into large mixer bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in black walnuts.
Turn batter into pans and spread evenly.
Bake at 375°
for 30 or 35 minutes following package directions for doneness test and cooling.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cook all ingredients except coconut over double boiler 7 minutes. Put coconut between layers and on top.

title: yeast rolls(grandma johnson's)
directions: In a large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Gradually add enough flour to make stiff.
Stir good each time flour is added. Pour on floured board and knead.
Put in a greased bowl.
Daub melted shortening on top to keep moist.
Let rise until double in bulk. Pour on floured board and knead. Pinch off dough and make rolls.
Brush melted shortening on top of rolls and let rise double in bulk.
Bake in 400° oven until done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat, don't boil.
Add a little milk, if too thick.

title: bugs on a log
directions: Wash celery and cut in 3-inch sections.
Mix peanut butter, milk and carrot in small bowl.
Stuff celery with peanut butter mixture and top each log with 2 raisins.
Makes 12 logs; 33 calories per log.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water 10 minutes; drain well. Place in 10 x 6 x 1 baking dish. Blend soup, milk and cheese; heat until the cheese melts. Pour over cabbage and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and sugar.
Pat into a 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan or a 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk and oil.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put rhubarb in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle with salt.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix in margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake until golden brown and rhubarb is tender, for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with flour combined with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Brown in fat in skillet.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Add to pork chops with green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with remaining salt. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour ingredients into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top pie crust.
Vent top of pie crust with 5 to 6 slits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in roaster.
Cover with foil and lid. Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Don't peek!

title: ham and cheese potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, celery, ham, cheese, onion, green pepper, salt and enough salad dressing to moisten.
Mix lightly. Chill.
Sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine pudding mix, juice concentrate and yogurt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yield:
28 (1 ounce) servings.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put cranapple juice and brown sugar in percolator.
Place cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and nutmeg in percolator basket and perk.

title: scalloped potatoes made easy
directions: Saute onion with bacon in skillet, stirring until bacon is crisp. Drain. Combine with potatoes in greased baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over top.
Mix gently. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken a la orange
directions: Combine flour with chili powder.
Coat chicken.
In 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, cook chicken until brown on all sides in butter.
Stir in remaining flour mixture, orange peel, orange juice, sugar and salt.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add orange sections and heat.
Serves four.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Flatten biscuits into 5-inch circles.
Press each into the bottom and up the sides of muffin cups and set aside.
In a skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
In a small bowl, mix catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder.
Stir until smooth and add to meat and mix well.
Divide meat mixture among biscuit-lined muffin cups, using about 1/4 cup for each.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from muffin pan. Yields 10 servings.

title: rainbow cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add baking soda, cream of tartar, milk, salt, vanilla and flour.

title: orange refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add orange rind and juice.
Stir in flour mixed with soda and salt.
Make into rolls, about 2 inches across.
Chill.
Slice 1/4 inch thick, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together in 9-inch pie dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat cakes
directions: Simmer onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add crumbs.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.
Shape into 3-inch patties.
Dust with bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat or brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons of butter on low heat for 6 minutes.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Use 1/2 teaspoon of the salt in potatoes.
Drain cooked potatoes and dice them.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion, garlic and remaining salt.
Fold into cooked potato cubes. Spread into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese, sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.
Very good!

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 200 to 250°.
Melt almond bark in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring very well.
Add peanut butter first in order for it to melt.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Yields about 60 cookies.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together the margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn the mixture into the pan.
Spoon pie filling into cake, in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and cake tests done.
Filling will sink into cake while baking.
Place bottom side up on serving plate.
Spoon slightly sweetened whipped cream over each serving if desired.
This is great served warm!

title: cream chess pie
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and flour.
Beat in eggs and milk thoroughly.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak into large cubes.
Melt the butter in a Dutch oven. When sizzling, brown the meat.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, covered.
For the last 15 minutes, uncover and stir several times.
If juice is too thin, increase heat so that excess moisture evaporates.
Remove bay leaf and serve over noodles or rice.

title: georgia fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add baking powder to flour, then sift twice.
Add 1 cup flour to nuts and fruit.
Add another cup of flour to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add lemon flavoring.
Mix flour, nuts and fruit together by hand.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Put into ungreased tube pan and place in cold oven.
Put pan of water on bottom shelf.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes. Sift flour; add soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Set aside.
Blend oil and egg into apple/sugar mixture.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Spread evenly in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oiled and heated iron skillet at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Butter and sugar a pie plate.
Cut refrigerator sugar cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices and lay out in bottom of pie dish. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple, water and sugar to boil.
Add apricot jello. Let cool.
Add cream cheese, celery and nuts.
When it starts to thicken, add Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Reserve 2 ounces white chocolate and oil.
Melt rest of chocolate.
Add marshmallows, peanuts, Rice Krispies and part of coconut. Spread on 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries. Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix 1 cup boiling water with Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Beat cranberry sauce and sour cream into Jell-O mixture.
Drain oranges; fold oranges and walnuts into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times; cream margarine and sugar, add molasses and add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately.
Use regular 9-inch cake pans.
Preheat and grease well.
Pour batter in bottom of pans as thin as you can to cover bottom of pan.
Makes 10 to 12 thin layers.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Stack using fresh applesauce between all layers and on top and sides.
This recipe is over 100 years old.

title: garden chicken
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Add vegetables and soup mix blended with water.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves two.

title: daisy corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake in oven 45 minutes at 300°.

title: berry cream coffee cake
directions: Cut cheese and butter into biscuit mix.
Blend in 1/3 cup milk.
Knead 8 to 10 strokes.
Roll into rectangle on waxed paper. Turn onto greased cookie sheet.
Remove waxed paper.
Spread preserves down center of rectangle.
Cut off sides of dough into strips (almost to jam).
Fold strips over center (crisscross). Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Drizzle with icing.

title: mock spiced apple rings
directions: Soak cucumber slices in the water and lime mixture 24 hours. Rinse well.
Soak 3 hours in clear water; drain.
Add vinegar, food coloring, alum and enough water to cover cucumbers. Simmer 2 hours and drain.
Heat 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, 1 cup red hots, 7 cups sugar and 4 cinnamon sticks until red hots melt. Pour over cucumber slices and let stand overnight.
Reheat and pack into jars.
Process for 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In oblong Pyrex dish, layer bean dip, guacamole dip, combination of sour cream, taco seasoning, mayo and dab of milk, grated Cheddar cheese, chopped green onions and sliced black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Cook bacon, break into pieces. Combine with beans.
Mix ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, liquid smoke, salt and pepper.
Add to beans and beef mixture.
Put in slow cooker 4 to 6 hours.

title: basil vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously; chill.
Just before serving, shake well and toss dressing with torn romaine, Bibb and red leaf lettuces.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix water and vinegar; pour over chicken wings in a baking dish with the wings in one layer.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on each wing.
Use 1 small bottle of soy sauce and cover each wing with the soy sauce.
Add garlic flakes on each wing (minced garlic may be substituted for garlic flakes, if desired, but do not use garlic salt).
Marinate for 1 or 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple juice, apple cider vinegar and egg in a saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Cool 1 hour or overnight in a small bowl.
Mix with apples, pineapple and nuts (reserve some nuts to cover salad as a topping).
Add Cool Whip and top with leftover nuts.
You can use 16 ounce Cool Whip to last a little longer.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream together butter, salt, brown sugar, eggs vanilla and baking powder. Mix in flour, oatmeal and cornflakes. Add nuts, chips and coconut. Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: pistachio-coconut surprise
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple and stir until blended.
Put into mold and freeze.
Dip in warm water and unmold onto serving plate.

title: chicken fruit salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Slice pineapple in half through fruit and leaves lengthwise (top to bottom).
Scoop out pineapple and cut fruit into 1-inch chunks.
Drain; combine fruit and chicken.
Toss lightly with dressing and chill.
Spoon into pineapple shells.
Sprinkle top with nuts and serve.

title: easy oven vegetables
directions: Combine beans, carrots, onions and cheese in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: neehams(candy)
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter.
Add milk, vanilla, powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix until well blended.
Roll into balls the size of small walnut.
Refrigerate.
Dip into melted Wilton chocolate to coat.

title: beans
directions: Brown together hamburger, onion and bacon.
Add catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, baked beans, lima beans, kidney beans and butter beans.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Do not overbake.

title: "blt" in a bowl
directions: Core, rinse and thoroughly drain lettuce; chill in disposable plastic bag.
Prepare Mustard Dressing.
Shortly before serving, line 4 individual serving bowls with a few outer lettuce leaves. Cut remaining lettuce into bite-sized chunks to measure 2 quarts. Combine with mushrooms, radish and onions.
Divide among the 4 bowls.
Top with egg slices and bacon strips.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Serve at once with Mustard Dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place torn lettuce as the first layer into a 9 x 13-inch plastic or glass container.
Add enough lettuce to cover the bottom of the dish.
Place each vegetable spread evenly over the lettuce, layer by layer.
Spread the mayonnaise like a thin frosting over the top layer of vegetables.
Sprinkle the brown sugar over the mayonnaise and add the shredded cheese evenly over the mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with a generous amount of bacon bits. Refrigerate.
The lettuce needs to be well drained or this will become very soggy!

title: cheddar cheese wafers
directions: Combine ingredients and knead into log shape.
Wrap and chill; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until brown or really set (firm).
I would check the bottoms.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain. Brown meat with onions. Add sauce and seasoning. Mix drained macaroni with egg and milk. Spread macaroni mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cover with meat. Bake until cheese melts, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: man-on-the-moon apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Add cooking oil and beat again. Then add sugar and vanilla and beat well. Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder. Add to egg mixture. Then add nuts and apples; mix well. Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. It may take longer depending on apples used.

title: no cook candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Shape candy into small balls or a log.
Serve.

title: meat loaf with veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients until well blended. Bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar, butter and vanilla; bring to a boil.
Once a boil starts, let it boil at a little lower heat for 7 or 8 minutes, stirring continuously while it is boiling.
After 7 or 8 minutes take off burner and add chocolate chips slowly, stirring while you add them, then add marshmallows, also stirring vigorously while adding them.
Then pour into rectangle cake pan or any large pan.
Let cool.
(If weather is hot, fudge is best kept in the refrigerator.)

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp and break into small pieces.
Add to beans. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°, stirring often, at least 1 hour.

title: honey thyme vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir into hot vegetables.
Add salt to taste.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Shape into large eggs. Freeze.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip eggs in chocolate with a large spoon or spatula, until covered with chocolate.
Lift onto wax paper.
Trim excess chocolate when hard. Decorate with favorite decorator icing.

title: peppers, onions and steak over rice
directions: Heat Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add steak and garlic.
Cook until browned.
Add tomatoes and one cup beef broth.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and green onions.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes. Combine remaining beef broth, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir until well blended.
Add to skillet.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings. Contains 520 calories, fat 19 g (171 cal or 33% of total calories), sat fat 4 g (7% of total calories), carb 47 g, protein 39 g, chol 95 mg and sodium 900 mg (*535).

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 package of pudding, oil, walnuts, eggs and club soda. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 X 13 pan. After cake cools, dissolve remaining pudding mix in cold milk. Add cool whip and beat until thick. Spread on cooled cake and refrigerate to let frosting set. Serve chilled.

title: mom's frittata di patate(potatoes)
directions: Peel and cut potatoes either in round slices or side slices. Wash the potatoes under cold water; drain.
Pat dry and season with salt and pepper.
Put a large, nonstick frying pan (or one sprayed with Pam) on medium-high heat.
When pan is hot, add enough oil to fully coat bottom of pan.
When oil is hot, add potatoes to the pan and fry on medium-high heat, turning them often so that all potatoes will be crispy and golden.

title: no bake coconut cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake in large or long Pyrex dish.
Mix instant pie filling according to instructions.
Add coconut; then pour over cake and mix thoroughly.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: beefy cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts.
Make into shape of a ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel them and let them cool. Boil and peel eggs. Slice potatoes as thin as possible. Add sliced eggs. Add thin sliced cucumber. Dice and fry bacon crisp. Add bacon with drippings. Add salt, pepper and vinegar to taste.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook and add spaghetti.
Stir so it doesn't stick.

title: sweet 'n sour pork chops
directions: Flour
pork
chops in Bisquick;
brown in a little oil. Simmer for 1 hour in sauce.
The sauce will thicken.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash potatoes; pare thinly and remove eyes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices to measure about 4 cups. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
In greased 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes in 2 layers, topping each with 1/2 the onion and 1/3 of the white sauce.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover; bake 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 60 to 70 minutes longer, or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, syrup, sugars, butter and vanilla.
Mix well; add nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and water.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Form small rolls, 1 1/2-inches long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
While hot, roll cookies in powdered sugar.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. May be frozen before baking.

title: broccoli-cauliflower tossed salad
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower over boiling water for 4 to 5 minutes covered until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Transfer them to large bowl.
Add lettuce and sweetened pepper.
Toss gently.
Combine chicken broth and remaining ingredients in small jar.
Cover tightly and shake to blend.
Pour over salad and toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: one pot pork chop dinner
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops.
Add rest of the ingredients. Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: sweet potato (squash) muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 1/4 cups sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sweet potatoes (squash) and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until moistened. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: pink peppermint angel food cake
directions: Make batter for angel food cake as directed, except during last 1/2 minute of mixing, add 1/4 teaspoon pure peppermint extract. Pour half of batter into pan.
Add 3 to 4 drops red food coloring to batter in bowl.
Fold in with 4 to 5 strokes (color does not have to be blended evenly).
Pour into pan; marble pink and white batters slightly.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Frost with our Fluffy White Frosting Mix.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar, flour, lemon peel and salt.
Fill pie shell.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Fry corn tortillas soft and drain all grease from them.
Brown hamburger meat.
Cook chili in separate pan.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, lay 6 tortillas flat; spread 1/2 of hamburger meat over tortillas, then spread 1/2 of onion and 1 can of green chilies over meat.
Pour 1/2 of chili over it; spread 1/2 of cheese over top.
Repeat steps and make second layer with remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers and tossed salad.

title: white chili
directions: Mix beans, broth, water, onion, garlic and salt. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 30 minutes. Top with cheese in serving bowls. Serves 6.
Contains 41.6 grams fat and 273 calories per cup.

title: gooey butter coffeecake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 2 beaten eggs and 1 stick of softened butter. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pat the mixture into the bottom of the pan and halfway up the sides to form a shell. Mix together 8 ounce package of softened cream cheese, 1 stick of butter and 2 eggs.
Mix well and add the box of confectioners sugar (reserving 1/2 cup for later).
Blend smooth and pour into shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and sprinkle with the reserved powdered sugar.
Cut into pieces when completely cool.

title: crescent apple quicks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir until apples are well coated.
Separate dough into 16 triangles.
Spoon about 1 rounded tablespoon of apple mixture onto the center of each triangle.
Fold the 3 points of dough over the filling overlapping like an envelope.
Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until deep golden brown in color.
Remove from pan to cool.
Add glaze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with onion, 1 can of soup, 1 can of chicken broth and beaten eggs.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chicken.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup with milk.
Pour over chicken and dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with raw veggies.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Boil chicken (season with salt and pepper), cool and debone. Make homemade roux by browning flour in cooking oil until dark brown (adjust the amount of cooking oil and flour if necessary). Add this to broth and stir completely.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper, sausage and chicken pieces.
Bring to a boil and then cook on low to medium heat for 30 minutes to an hour.
Serve over rice with crackers.

title: quick chicken a la king
directions: Cook mushroom pieces, onion and green pepper in butter until onion and green pepper are tender.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add chicken, pimientos and pepper.
Heat slowly, stirring often. Serve in individual pastry shells, over toast or over rice. Serves 6.

title: pineapple salad in can
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions, except use only 1 can of water.
For other liquid, use pineapple juice, which has been drained out of can.
Pour Jell-O into can; chill until set. Run a little hot water on sides to loosen Jell-O, or cut bottom from can and push salad through.
Cut between pineapple slices. Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, sour cream, oil, salt, vanilla and eggs. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour small amount of batter into pan.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Add part of the brown sugar mixture to the pan.
Continue layering until both mixtures are used up.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Drizzle with 1 cup of powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon milk mixture.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, remove from skillet, add following to drippings:
4 large onions (sliced thin), 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 tablespoon dry mustard, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 cup vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes.
Drain dried butter beans, green lima beans, and dark red kidney beans.
Add pork and beans (do not drain).
Mix all beans together, add bacon and onion sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or crockpot 6 - 7 hours on low.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients, blending until smooth.
Fold in egg white.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Fry on hot griddle just like pancakes.
Serve with syrup.
Substitute 1/4 cup Egg Beaters and reduce oil to 1 tablespoon for low-fat corn cakes.
Makes 6 to 10 cakes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, bananas and chopped pecans. Bake at 350° in a greased pan; 2 (9-inch) layers for 25 to 30 minutes or a 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost, when cool, with cream cheese frosting.

title: lemon supreme cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients.
(Do not use mixer.)
Put two cups of powdered sugar in small bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls in powdered sugar; roll and shape balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 300° (do not overcook).
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: easy punch recipe
directions: Mix carefully in large pitcher, then pour into punch bowl so as not to spill around punch bowl.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add Mexican beans, shredded cheese and lettuce, broken into bite-size pieces.
Cover with Catalina salad dressing.
Be sure to use Catalina.
Just before serving, toss with Fritos.

title: slaw
directions: Chop or shred vegetables. Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and cover let cool.
Put in refrigerator overnite.
Drain before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches into bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and set aside.
Mix together butter, 1 cup sugar and flour.
Sprinkle flour mixture over top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until lightly brown on top.

title: walnut meringue pie
directions: Roll out 17 Ritz crackers (very fine crumbs).
Mix with 2 cups finely chopped walnuts.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add baking powder and continue beating until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold in sugar, gradually by hand.
Gently fold in the Ritz crackers and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
When cool, cover with whipped cream and shaved chocolate (semi-sweet).

title: seasoned salt mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1/4 cup seasoned salt mixture. Handy all-purpose season for camp cooking.

title: donuts
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and let stand until bubbly. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Let stand until double.
Roll on slightly floured surface until about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut donuts.
Let rise slightly.
Fry in cooking oil until brown.
Glaze while hot with powdered sugar glaze with vanilla extract.
Let excess drain off.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat; mix all ingredients. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. After an hour, sprinkle 1 can chow mein noodles over the top. Return to oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oven in an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish while oven preheats.
In blender, mix milk, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Remove pan from oven. Spread batter evenly in pan.
Pour batter over melted butter. Do not stir.
Pour fruit evenly over batter. Do not stir. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until crust is brown.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl. Add pasta.
Mix well to coat.
Refrigerate.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Pop corn and set aside in a shallow baking pan.
Boil together syrup, brown sugar, butter and vinegar for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda, vanilla and nuts. Stir well.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake 1 hour, stirring each 15 minutes.
Break apart while warm.
Cool before serving.

title: chunky chicken tetrazzini
directions: Make a roux with flour and butter.
Add chicken broth slowly until thick.
Lower heat and add cheese until melted.

title: cheddar chicken divine
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from bone.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange chicken and broccoli in baking dish (11 x 7 1/4-inch).

title: margarita pie
directions: Prepare pie shell using ingredients in package and following label directions.

title: cooked carrots kids will eat!
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil.
Add carrots; bring back to a boil.
Now add honey and brown sugar, stir until dissolved, then add a small amount of maple syrup.
Simmer for approximately 30 minutes, or until carrot slices are tender.
Serve in a small bowl with a little of the juice.

title: rhea burt's gobs
directions: Mix and drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool, then fill with icing.

title: easy barbecue meatballs
directions: Put all in crock pot and simmer on low.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat, drain and add seasonings.
Add boiling water, tomato sauce and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add celery, carrots and split peas.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Add macaroni.
Cook 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and serve. Serves 10.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa, milk and butter; add nuts. Spread in 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Cover with 1 3/4 cups hot water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy zucchini pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread mustard evenly over bottom of crust. Melt butter in large skillet.
Add zucchini and onions and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in parsley, basil, garlic powder and oregano; cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes. Combine eggs and cheese, stir into zucchini mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add chopped up chocolate squares.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amounts of hot mixture into yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pastry shell.
Add meringue and bake until golden brown.

title: wild berry buckle
directions: Put flour and 1 1/2 Tbsp. sugar in food processor, add chilled butter and process until mixture becomes crumbly.
With processor running, slowly pour in soda water, mixing until mixture forms a ball.
If mixing by hand, cut butter into flour and sugar; slowly add soda water, mixing with a fork.
Press dough mixture into a 4 inch circle; wrap in plastic wrap, and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
On a floured surface roll out to fit a 9 inch round or 11 x 7 inch baking dish allowing a 2 inch overhang.
Pour berries into crust; sprinkle sugar over fruit, dot with butter.
Drizzle bourbon over fruit.
Fold edges of crust over fruit, leaving center open.
Sprinkle with additional sugar if desired.
Bake at 425 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve at room temperature with Vanilla Cream Sauce.

title: devil's food brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with lots of garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dredge chicken pieces in seasoned flour. Fry, browning on all sides.
Meanwhile, place all but one garlic clove in a heavy Dutch oven.
Place browned chicken over garlic.
Sprinkle liberally with parsley, thyme, sage, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Place the remaining garlic clove in a small pan with the butter and simmer to melt.
Pour the garlic butter over the chicken.
Cover the Dutch oven.

title: meringue chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips. Preheat oven to 300° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven off and put cookies in oven overnight.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand a few minutes. Combine butter, vanilla, eggs and both sugars.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Bake in lightly buttered long baking pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
While cake is still hot, pour topping over top. Run it under the broiler long enough to slightly brown.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add egg.
Blend in carrots, lemon juice, sifted flour, baking powder and soda last.
Bake in buttered ring mold at 350° for one hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Melt jello and cream cheese in 1 cup hot water.
Mix in all other ingredients and chill.

title: trees and raisins salad
directions: Combine vegetables, raisins and kernels in a large bowl. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetable mixture. Stir to coat well.
Cover and set in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Sprinkle bacon just before serving.

title: cooked cornmeal mush
directions: Mix cornmeal, cold water and salt.
Slowly stir cornmeal mixture into the boiling water in a saucepan. Cook and stir until thick.
Lower heat; cover and cook for 15 minutes, stirring as needed to keep from sticking.
Makes 6 servings (1/2 cup each).

title: applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add applesauce.
Chill.
You can unmold on platter with lettuce, nuts and celery.

title: cheese angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and 2 tablespoons warm water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk to the yeast mixture and set aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: roger's favorite lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, and cool whip in large bowl until smooth. Pour into pie crust. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: french picnic loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except watercress and French bread in large bowl; mix well.
Shape into loaf in rectangular baking pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven until meat thermometer inserted into center registers 170°, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on wire rack; refrigerate until cold.
Garnish with watercress; serve with French bread.

title: turnip salad casserole
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit tea
directions: Boil tea bags in 2 cups water.
Pour into gallon jug.
Add other ingredients and fill rest of jug with water to make 1 gallon.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender and drain. In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Mix milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and green onions in oleo. Brown flour in oil.
When flour browns, turn to low.
Add okra. Fry sausage (sliced thin).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken (cooked and deboned into large pieces).
Add broth to pot.
Add sausage, gumbo file, garlic salt, tomatoes, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, crab boil and cream of mushroom soup. Simmer until almost done; add tuna in water and cut up ham and shrimp.

title: shish-ka-bob marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate steak several hours.
Brush on while cooking.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion (chopped) and spices.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer lasagna noodles in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake additional 15 minutes.
Let set several minutes before serving.

title: baked onions sliced in cheese with cream of chicken soup
directions: Slice onions and fry light yellow in butter.
Grate or slice cheese over top of onions which you have placed in casserole. Cover with soup and milk.
Top with slices of French bread and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bernice's banana punch
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a boil and continue to boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool and then add frozen orange juice, pineapple juice and the juice of a lemon.
Put the bananas through a blender and add to mixture.
Freeze.
Thaw out 3 hours before time to serve.
Put in punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Yields 60 servings.

title: mexichini salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and use as a salad or stuffing in pita bread sandwiches.
Also use for tacos or enchiladas.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with hands. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and pour over peanut butter mixture.

title: potato surprise
directions: Leaving hash browns frozen, mix all ingredients together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with French fried onions. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets and some stem into medium size pieces. Drain to dry completely.
Put raisins into boiling water and drain immediately.
Mix salad dressing, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over broccoli and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix again before serving.
Crisp bacon bits or sunflower seeds may be added.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cup blueberries into pie crust.
Spread evenly and set aside.
Combine 1 cup blueberries, sugar, cornstarch and water in medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour over blueberries in pie crust.
Chill.
Spoon whipped topping around edge. Garnish with 1/4 cup fresh blueberries.

title: spinach sausage cheese pie
directions: Place chicken pieces in large, shallow baking pan, skin side up.
(Use a pan about 15 x 10 x 2-inch.)
Brush with corn oil. Bake, uncovered, in a 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hot cottage potato salad
directions: Mix together and season with salt and pepper.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Over top, pour butter and milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Cube chicken, then brown in oil.
Add garlic and green pepper; saute briefly.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, sugar and pineapple with juice.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Add drained water chestnuts.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken until tender, then tear in small strips or pieces.
Combine celery and onions in saucepan and cook on low heat until tender.
Add
to
this mixture mushrooms (drained), bean sprouts (drained),
water chestnuts (drained) and cooking oil.
Simmer.
Separately
mix
soy
sauce,
chicken
broth, cornstarch and water.
Blend
with
celery
and onion mixture, when it is thoroughly done.
Continue simmering.
Add chicken. Serve over rinsed,
drained,
cooked
rice.
Top
with Chinese noodles.

title: asparagus in blankets
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Spread each slice generously with Hollandaise Sauce.
Place 2 asparagus spears diagonally on each slice and sprinkle generously with shredded cheese.
Fold bread diagonally over asparagus and secure with toothpick.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a preheated 400° oven for 12 minutes.

title: martin's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onion.
Mix in small bowl the mushroom and tomato soups.
Layer meat, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: nana's potato filling
directions: Place bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch pan and dot with butter. Brown in oven until golden.
Brown onions in butter or margarine. Add celery and cook until tender.
Add 1/2 cup water, simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add all ingredients to potatoes; add 2 or 3 raw eggs, parsley, salt and pepper to taste and 1 cup hot milk.
Bake at 350° until heated through and golden brown on top.
If turkey broth is available, pour a small amount on top to flavor before baking.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: simple spinach quiche
directions: Defrost spinach and drain/squeeze out all water.
Melt margarine over spinach in the microwave.
Mix in onion soup and black pepper (to taste).
Beat eggs in a separate bowl.
Add milk, eggs and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Place on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Check with a toothpick to see when it is well done (it should be dry).

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Add one juice can of water to thawed juice.
Mix in other ingredients.
Add grapes, bananas, apples or whatever.
Sweeten to taste.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Saute onion, bacon and green beans.
Mix brown sugar and catsup.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Can also be cooked in microwave or for shorter time at higher temperature in regular oven.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In the morning, parboil them for 10 minutes with a teaspoon of baking soda. Run cold water through the beans in a colander or strainer.
Dice a rind of salt pork in 1-inch squares.
Divide into 2 portions.
Put half of the pork in the bottom of a 2-quart bean pot with whole onion.
Put beans into pot.
Put the rest of the pork on top.
Mix all other ingredients with water and pour over the beans.
Put in a 300° oven for 6 hours.
Makes 10 portions.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting time when mixture comes to a hard boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well until blended. Spoon out on waxed paper and cool.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Mix flour, eggs, sugar, pumpkin spices and lemon juice. Grease and lightly flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Loosen edges; turn out on towel.
Starting at narrow end, roll cake in towel.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oranges.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes at low speed.
Bake at 350° for 30
to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make topping while cake is baking.

title: sausage and minestrone soup
directions: In large pot, brown sausage, onion and garlic.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except beans, spaghetti and cheese. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour. Stir in beans and pasta.
Bring back to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, until beans are tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and Jell-O.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add strawberries, salt and vanilla; mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: icebox hot rolls
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into a mixer.
Beat well.
Then add water and flour.
Work flour into this mixture.
Turn on floured board and knead.
Grease a large bowl; put bread mixture in.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Put in icebox to raise.
Take out, pinch any amount off and put remainder back in icebox.
Make rolls.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onion with salt and let stand 1 hour. Add vinegar and spices and cinnamon stick and cook 10 minutes. Remove cinnamon stick. Place in clean hot jars and seal.

title: crab orleans casserole
directions: Saute veggies in butter until tender.
Blend in soup and broth; add rice, crabmeat, lemon juice, seasonings and eggs.
Mix well.
Turn into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 cups.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook sugar, water and rhubarb together until rhubarb is tender.
Add 1 box strawberry jello.
Refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into bowl and chill to set.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Rinse blender container with hot water.
Place marshmallows and chocolate powder in blender container.
Cover and blend on a low speed; remove cover and insert.
While adding milk, continue to blend at low speed.
Serve immediately.

title: flan
directions: In medium, rounded glass baking dish, pour in sugar.
Place in heated oven until sugar has caramelized.
Remove from oven and rotate dish, allowing caramelized sugar to run up sides of baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into baking dish.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with cinnamon.

title: chocolate bar pie
directions: Mix chocolate bar, milk and marshmallows; heat until melted, stirring until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Whip the heavy or whipping cream until stiff; fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill several hours, until firm.
May garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well and allow to stand, covered, in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours.
Yield: 2 1/4 cups.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine onion, broccoli and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Add margarine, cottage cheese and salt; mix well.
Stir in cornbread mix until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish or muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, vegetable oil and sugar; blend well.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts. Beat well.
Pour into an 8-inch or 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pour topping over it in the pan and let it cool.
When cooled, remove from pan.

title: coffee squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and salt together.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: beer batter mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Heat oil in deep fat fryer (2 to 3-inches) at 375°.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Combine melted butter, egg yolks and remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Fold egg whites into mixture.
Dip each mushroom into batter, letting excess drip into bowl.
Fry a few mushrooms at a time in hot oil until golden brown.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes more.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoons. Crisscross each drop with a floured fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: chicken cordon bleu casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with ham.
Put cheese slices on top of ham.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and water; stir with a wire whisk until smooth.
Add mayonnaise mixture to chicken mixture.
Gently fold in egg slices. Spoon mixture into a greased 13-inch by 9-inch baking dish; top with potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20-25 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eight layer dip
directions: Mix beans and picante sauce.
Spread over lettuce; then add a layer of sour cream, guacamole, cheese, onion, olives and tomatoes.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine all except candy.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with candy kiss.
Press down so cookie cracks around edge.
Yield:
about 48 cookies.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and stir until dissolved.
Add boiling water; stir.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple, including the juice.
Chill until partially set.
Whip 2 packages of Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold into gelatin mixture. Line a large, round mixing bowl with wax paper.
Cut or break the angel food cake into small pieces.
Place a layer of cake pieces in bowl, then a layer of the gelatin mixture, alternating until all is used.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, turn cake out on large cake plate.
Whip other package of Dream Whip and spread over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with cherries.

title: night cookies
