directions: Mix into dough.
Make into roll at night.
Refrigerate.
Slice 1/4-inch thick next morning.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hummingbird food
directions: Boil for 4 minutes.
Let cool.
Fill hummingbird feeder. Feeders should stay out until Labor Day to allow the birds to get to warmer climates before cold weather sets in.

title: quicky quiche
directions: Remove crust from sandwich bread.
Lay slices on bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
On top put in layers (2 layers) the cheese, chilies and sausage.
Mix eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk, salt and pepper. Pour over the first mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix soup and 1/4 cup milk and pour over mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pans.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto batter.
Cut through batter with knife or metal spatula several times for marbled effect.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and chopped nuts if desired.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center or when wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tortellini in white sauce
directions: Saute Prosciutto in butter.
Add milk; bring to slow boil. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook on low until it begins to thicken.
Add heavy cream and continue to cook on low for 8 minutes.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Brown and drain meats.
(I wash my meats with warm water in a colander to remove all grease.)
Drain all beans and combine with meats.
Mix tomato sauce, mustard and brown sugar; pour over meat and beans.
Mix well.
Bake in an uncovered dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cover because it will collect moisture and make it all soupy.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix in well drained pineapple and pecans.
Spread in prepared crust and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sweet-sour cocktail sausages
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1 cup of juice.
In large skillet, blend sugar, flour and mustard.
Stir in pineapple juice, soy sauce and vinegar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.

title: ethel's pie pastry
directions: Put eggs and vinegar in a cup.
Beat well.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Mix all dry ingredients together with lard, cut in well.
Add egg, vinegar and water mixture.
Mix only until blended.
Roll out on floured board.

title: amaretto delicious cake
directions: Grease a
Bundt
or
tube
pan	and put chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Combine cake mix with pudding mix, water, oil, Amaretto and eggs; mix well.
Pour into pan over nuts and bake at 350°
for 50
to
55 minutes.
Just before cake is through baking, combine the
sugar,
butter
and 1/2 cup Amaretto and boil for
5 minutes.
Immediately upon taking cake from oven, pour over the cake.
Let cool in pan 1 to 2 hours.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook, crumble and drain sausage.
Line pie shells with sausage.
Beat eggs.
Blend in milk, dry mustard, salt, cheese and sour cream.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This quiche freezes well.
If quiche is frozen, do not thaw before baking.

title: bohemian cottage cheese dumplings(plum or peach)
directions: Put the cottage cheese through a sieve or a ricer.
Add the eggs and a pinch of salt.
Mix together with cheese.
Gradually add flour until dough is a medium consistency.
Make a small dumpling into which a peach or a blue plum is put in the center. Boil dumplings in salted water for about 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Serve with melted butter, sugar, cinnamon and additional cheese.

title: crunchy chicken parmesan
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Dip chicken in egg, then mixture. Put in pan and drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using mixer on medium.
Put a teaspoon of oil in each of 12 muffin pans.
Put in oven until hot (smoking).
Add batter mix (approximately 1/2 full).
Bake at 425° until batter puffs, then lower oven to 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot from oven with roast beef dinner.

title: joe's special meat marinade
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
May be used with beef or chicken (chunks or whole).
Marinate 4 to 24 hours.

title: millet milk
directions: Blend until smooth.
Add enough water to make 6 cups of milk.

title: five alive angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions except substitute the Five Alive for the amount of water.
Bake and cool as directed.
Remove from pan and drizzle with Glaze or powdered sugar icing using Five Alive for the liquid.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Arrange nuts in pie shell. Beat eggs.
Add and blend syrup, butter and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour.
Blend with egg mixture and pour over nuts in pie shell. Let stand until nuts rise, so they'll get a nice glaze during baking.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon, onions, pepper and rice in bacon fat (high heat); add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer 15 minutes.

title: savory sauce for fish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve at once.

title: cabbage pickles
directions: Combine vegetables and salt in large bowl.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain.
Blend together sugar, mustard, cornstarch, celery seed and turmeric in large kettle.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to boiling.
Add drained vegetables; return to boiling.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Immediately ladle into 8 hot pint jars, filling to within 1/4 inch from the top.
Adjust lids.

title: oatmeal yeast loaves
directions: Combine oats and boiling water in mixing bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugar, butter and salt.
Stir until butter smooths. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir yeast mixture and 2 cups flour into oats mixture.
Gradually stir remaining flour into batter.
Knead about 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place (about 1 hour or until double in bulk).
Punch down and divide in half.
Shape each half into loaf.
Bake each loaf at 350° for 30 minutes or until hollow when tapped.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until done; remove cooked vegetables and mash well.
Return to water.
Add milk, pepper and salt. Reheat just before serving.
Crumble bacon and float bacon and parsley on soup.
Serves 6.

title: oven "fried" chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in dressing for one hour; refrigerated.
Roll chicken breast in corn flakes, covering chicken.
Place chicken in well-greased casserole (Pam works fine.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade freezer ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and salt and beat again.
Stir in half and half and vanilla.
Pour into 5-quart ice cream freezer container and add milk until reaches the fill line.
Freeze according to machine directions.

title: finnish biscuit
directions: Mix together.
Add flour, stirring, until thick.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise in greased bowl until double (cover with plastic wrap).
Shape as desired (buns, cinnamon, rolls or coffee cake) or rolls as if making cinnamon rolls.
Don't cut.
Put in round pan; make circle.
Slash with scissors.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (rolls 25 minutes).
Frost with powdered sugar icing, nuts and cherries or 1/3 cup hot coffee with 2 tablespoons sugar.
For glaze, sprinkle with sugar.

title: broccoli and shrimp salad
directions: Parboil rice; drain, then cook in chicken stock.
To the cooked rice, add broccoli, shrimp, almonds, 1 1/2 tablespoons minced parsley and 1 1/2 tablespoons chives.
Mix rest of the ingredients except oil until smooth.
Slowly whisk in oil.
Pour over salad and chill.
Garnish with thin strips of pimento.

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Using taco seasoning, prepare meat following package directions.
Add tomato sauce.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, chilies and olives in a bowl.
Crush 1/2 package of chips and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 cheese mixture and 1 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat layers, finishing with Monterey Jack cheese.
Top with crushed chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken and return to oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and knead on floured surface for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
After standing, pull off pieces and stretch to desired size.
A rolling pin works well for stretching.
Flatten dough with hands and fry in hot oil until lightly browned.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: scones
directions: Note:
Add a dash of vinegar to the sour cream.

title: mexican salad
directions: Line salad bowl with drained beans.
Layer the chopped onion over the beans.
Layer the chopped bell pepper over the onion. Layer the chopped tomatoes over the bell pepper.
Top with shredded cheese.
Ten minutes before serving, crush corn chips while still in the bag.
Layer chips on top of salad.
Pour the dressing over chips and toss.
Ready to serve.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with a meat mallet.
Set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in 2/3 cup stuffing mix, water, salt and pepper.
Spread stuffing mixture evenly on each chicken breast.
Roll up chicken breast. Secure with wooden picks.

title: squash custard
directions: Boil squash until it can be mashed.
Drain the squash; melt butter in hot squash.
In a separate bowl, combine egg yolks, 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and vanilla.
Stir well and add evaporated milk and water; add to squash and mix well.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until firm, about 1 hour.
Remove from heat.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In a large bowl combine cucumbers, onion and red peppers. Sprinkle with salt and mix well.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
In a medium bowl combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Place cucumber mixture in nonmetallic container.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers.
Cover and chill for at least 24 hours to blend flavors.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Prepare long grain and wild rice according to package directions.
Refrigerate.
Prepare salad dressing according to package directions.
Add soy sauce and sugar to prepared Italian dressing; shake to mix thoroughly.

title: never fail caramel-korn
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil five minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popped popcorn in two shallow pans or cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for one hour, stirring and coating every 15 minutes.
(Does not stick together and keeps well in closed container.)

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning mix and 1/2 cup water. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Separate rolls and press into a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle half of chips over crust.
Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle on remaining corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no bake cookies(boiled cookies)
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, sugar, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes after rolling boil starts. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Pour cocoa mixture over oatmeal.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture onto wax paper. Let sit until hard.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder, grated zucchini, salt and nuts.
Bake 2 loaves at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in 13 x 9-inch or sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Spread while warm with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: taco joe dip
directions: In a slow cooker, combine ingredients. Cook on low 4 to 6 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Put small amount of oatmeal in blender at a time and blend until it turns into powder.
Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and cook at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: sausage and potatoes breakfast
directions: Beat together the eggs and milk.
Place crescent rolls in pie plate.
Brown sausage and drain.
Place on crescent rolls.
Defrost potatoes and put on sausage.
Sprinkle green peppers and onions over sausage.
Add cheese, then egg and milk mixture.
Bake until brown at 300°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the mushrooms, pepper, pimento, celery, olive slices and onion.
Mix sauteed mixture, chicken pieces and spaghetti with the soups, Worcestershire sauce, Velveeta, garlic salt and salt and pepper.
When well mixed, refrigerate.
Cook 40 minutes at 250°. (May take longer if mixture remains in refrigerator several hours.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with celery and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Take chicken off bones and place chicken in greased casserole. Add cream of chicken soup to 1/2 cup milk.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Heat 1 cup broth from boiled chicken with 1 stick margarine.
Add to stuffing mix.
Place this dressing on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frothy fruit shake
directions: Put ice in food processor and blend until only chips exist. Throw in strawberries, bananas, pineapple, peach and milk.
Blend until consistent thickness (the longer you blend the thinner it becomes).
Pour into cup and drink.
Makes roughly 2 quarts. Fat-free and filling.

title: hamburger casserole au gratin
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil potatoes, peel and slice.
Thin the soup with 1 can of milk.
Add in layers: first potatoes, then meat, cheese, onion rings and soup.
Make 3 layers in all, ending with onion rings.
Warm at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: easy easter strawberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease one 15 x 10 x 1/2-inch cookie pan.
Sift together 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream together sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat on low speed until crumbly.
Add almonds, lemon peel and eggs.
Stir with fork until evenly moistened.
Remove 1 cup dough; set aside.
Pat remaining dough in pan.
Spread jam over dough. Keep 1/2-inch from sides.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup flour with remaining dough; crumble over top.
Bake 22 to 27 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add seasonings and tomato sauce. In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce, olives and cheese.
Add water and cover.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: okra casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop the eggs and tomatoes.
Fry the skillet of breaded okra.
Saute the peppers and onion.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: herb chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 325°, turning once after 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally, turn skin side up.
Cover and bake 30 minutes more or until tender.
Also good with skinless chicken.

title: snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat whites until thick and frothy.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Stir in salt, chips and nuts.
Drop heaping teaspoons on foil-lined cookie sheets.
Place cookies in oven and turn oven off.
No peeking!! Leave overnight or until oven cools down (6 to 8 hours).

title: three-herb popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large container or oven roasting pan.
Salt to taste and set aside.
Melt butter in small saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in basil, chervil and thyme.
Drizzle butter mixture over popcorn and toss lightly to coat evenly.
Stir in the nuts, if desired.
Makes about 20 cups.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add egg whites; beat well. Blend in peanut butter and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Stir in chopped candy bars. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks.

title: oven beef patties
directions: Form beef into 6 patties.
Place in broiler pan.
Pour onion soup mix over patties.
Spoon mushroom soup on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy herb baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or line with foil 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, onion powder, garlic salt, paprika and pepper; stir until well mixed.
Dip chicken pieces into margarine; roll in potato flake mixture to coat. Place in pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: amaretto slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a container and freeze at least overnight.
To serve, put some slush in glass; add 7-Up or wine.

title: puppy chow
directions: In double boiler, melt butter, peanut butter and chips. Pour over cereal and stir until well coated. (Add pecans here, if desired.) Dump into paper sack or small plastic garbage bag and add powdered sugar. Toss until well coated. Remove and spread on waxed paper to dry.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Combine rind, juice and sugar. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Add lemon slices and water. Add ice just before serving. Makes 6 servings. This is really good on a hot day!

title: hot broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions in a large saucepan; drain well. Add remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 1 quart.

title: the chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend into cream mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugars.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice thin.
Bake in a hot 425° oven for about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: chili burritos
directions: Warm flour tortillas.
Heat chili.
Place 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon of chili in center of each tortilla.
Top with shredded lettuce and diced tomato.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and roll tortilla to enclose filling.
Top tortilla with 1 tablespoon of sour cream, 1 teaspoon chopped green onion and 1 teaspoon of grated cheese.

title: ma's berries and cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt butter in bottom of deep baking dish (in oven).
Mix the dry ingredients together.
Add milk; mix. Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour berries or fruit on batter; do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Good served warm.

title: mom's cherry angel treat
directions: Slice angel food cake into three layers after it is frozen. Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Blend in cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spread mixture between layers, on top and on sides.
Spoon (drizzle) pie filling over top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: make-up remover
directions: *Cut one roll in half.

title: easy baked sweet-sour chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken, skin down, in greased shallow baking dish.
Combine oil, honey, lemon juice, paprika and mustard in small bowl; baste chicken with sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and brush with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce and margarine until melted.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aunt martha's cheese squares
directions: Remove crust from bread and cut into 1-inch squares.
In double boiler, melt cheese and margarine.

When creamy, fold in egg whites. Dip cubes into mixture and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, place in plastic bag and keep in freezer. To serve, bake at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: spicy italian salad
directions: Cook elbows according to package directions; drain well. Cool.
Combine cooled elbows, tomato wedges, pepperoni, cheese, green pepper, celery, onion and salad dressing; toss lightly. Place in a lettuce-lined bowl and garnish with ripe olive halves, if desired.
Cover and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat the egg with a fork.
Add in milk and oil.
In a small bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir flour mixture into egg.
Do not overmix; batter should be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill 6 paper lined muffin cups for large muffins (or 12 for smaller muffins).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tester comes out clean and tops are brown.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Roll cookies in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or so.
Let cookies cool and then roll in sugar.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt the butter on low with garlic, medium heat.
Pour in cream; melt.
Add cheese; melt.
Serve over fettuccine or tortellini.
Makes 4 to 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill 9 x 12-inch dish with chopped lettuce.
Sprinkle with diced onion, chopped celery and chopped green pepper.
Add package of frozen peas.
In a separate bowl, mix together sugar and Miracle Whip.
Spread dressing over salad.
Top with shredded cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
This can be made early morning on the day of serving.

title: cornbread with mayo
directions: Beat well.
Pour into skillet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot wassail punch
directions: Heat, strain and discard spices.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Toss and chill for several hours before serving.

title: three bean bake
directions: Brown meat (if using bacon, drain fat) and onion.
Do not drain beans.
Stir and mix all together.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or cook on top of stove for a half hour.
You may mix half bacon and half hamburg for a smoke flavor.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Roll in balls.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Prepare lemon jello.
When it starts to thicken, mix in the drained crushed pineapple, but save the juice.
Let set until jelled.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Saute sausage in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add pepper, onion and celery in skillet.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in large saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add sausage, soup mix and salt.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: oven baked possum
directions: Skin possum,
then
rub
salt
and
pepper all over the body. Then run
a mixture of vinegar and brown sugar over the body. Then
place
in
refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, put the pan and possum
on	top of the stove.
Add 4 spoons of bacon fat and sear
him
on
all
sides.
Then
add
onions to possum.
Put in oven
and
bake	for 1 hour at 350°.
Take him out of the oven and turn him over and add sweet potatoes.
Use plenty of potatoes. Then put him back	in
the
oven and cook another 2 hours or until he is tender.

title: oreo cookie "dirt" cake
directions: Set aside 24 whole Oreo cookies.
Crumble remaining Oreos in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbled cookies.
Place 24 whole Oreos on cream cheese layer.
Mix instant pudding according to directions on package and pour over cake.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: hoppin john 'n' sausages
directions: Bake sausage one layer deep in pan, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Drain sausage drippings into large skillet; stir-fry onion and pepper until tender.
Place in large bowl.
Add sausage, rice, peas, salt and pepper and bacon drippings.
Pour in casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taffy apple salad(makes 8-10 servings.)
directions: Separate pineapple juice and crushed pineapple (don't throw out juice).
Combine drained pineapple and marshmallows. Refrigerate overnite.
Beat pineapple juice, egg, flour, vinegar & sugar.
Heat until thick, stirring (takes a while).
Refrigerate overnite. Next day, mix sauce & cool whip.
Add peanuts, marshmallow mix & apples, stir.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Chop and add the bell pepper, onion, cauliflower, celery and carrots.
Drain the remaining ingredients and add.
Marinate at least 24 hours. Serves 20 to 25.

title: quick bake beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon; add remaining ingredients in 4-quart pan.
Cook for about 1/2 hour on low.

title: tomato soup
directions: Skin the tomatoes by plunging them in boiling water and peeling.
Saute the chopped onion in the butter and add the tomatoes and stock.
Simmer for about 15 minutes and add seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in blender and liquefy, then strain to remove the seeds.
Add the cream and heat but don't boil.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Grease two pie plates and divide mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zatoni
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add other ingredients.
Pat onto large casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
You can freeze part of this for another day.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Put everything in blender until mixed.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate that has been sprayed with Mazola oil spray.
Bake at 350° until done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grape leaves
directions: Mix rice, tomatoes, ground lamb, salt and pepper altogether. Set aside.
Take lamb bones and spread around the bottom of kettle.
Take grape leaves, one at a time, and lay flat.
Scoop a spoon of rice mixture on leaf.
Roll up tight and place on top of lamb bones.
Cover the pan of leaves with part water and part tomatoes.
Cover and cook until done, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jew bread
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs together; heat slightly.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in a greased sheet pan. Bake at 325° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and cook in deep hot grease.

title: quaker's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie, 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken in dish, spooning with sauce mixture to cover.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Prepare meat and taco seasoning as directed on package.
If using onion, brown in small amount of oil, then add ground beef. Brown and drain.
Add 1/2 cup cheese (chunks or shredded) and can of tomato soup, plus other chosen ingredients.
Simmer until cheese is melted and all ingredients are heated.
Grease cookie sheet or sheet cake pan.
Put desired amount of meat mixture in shell.
Roll and place in pan.
Place open end of shell on pan bottom to prevent unrolling.
Pour 2 cans of tomato sauce over top; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: glorified chicken and rice
directions: You may also use poultry seasoning.

title: caramel apples
directions: Insert a wooden skewer into each apple (washed and dried). Set aside.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, milk and salt.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring gently but constantly to 230° on candy thermometer or until small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Working quickly, dip apples in caramel to coat well.
Place apples, stem side up, to harden on buttered wax paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cheese and butter. Add blue cheese crumbs, then olives and chives. Cool. Make into ball and roll into chopped walnuts.

title: tamale pie(8 to 10 servings)
directions: First before chopping tomatoes with sharp knife, start a top of tomato and peel around top layer of skin. Will curl like a rose for center of dish. In 10-inch square baking dish, layer as follows. Mix first 2 ingredients for bottom layer. Mash avocados; blend lemon juice, mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix. Spread over bean dip. Add cheese. Sprinkle chopped scallions. Put tomato rose in middle. Put olives around edge of dish. Fill in with chopped tomatoes. Refrigerate to combine flavors. Serve with favorite tortilla chips or crackers. Dip to reach all layers. Enjoy.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to cream mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla; add nuts and coconut. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased pans.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Heat in microwave for 20 minutes or on top of stove. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Strain off spices.
Pour back in jug. Store in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 weeks.
Use as needed.
Heat 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Cream until light and fluffy. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternating with the Orange Crush.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pecan squares
directions: Beat 1 egg well and gradually add flour.
Spread this mixture on a well-greased baking sheet, 11 x 16-inches.
Beat well 1 egg and spread on.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup dark brown sugar on.
Spread over this 1 cup or more chopped pecans.
Sprinkle over this 1/2 cup dark brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Grandma Hill's recipe.)

title: macadamia white chocolate muffins
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and baking powder.
In separate bowl, combine milk, butter and egg.
Make a well in flour and stir in liquid.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all together; add ice.

title: dill dip
directions: Chop dried beef into small pieces.
Blend all other ingredients well.
Add chopped beef.
Let set in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.

title: cheese olive balls
directions: Have cheese and margarine at room temperature; blend well. Mix in seasonings thoroughly.
Cut in flour (best to crumble by hand).
Chill dough for 20 minutes.
Drain the olives.
Pinch off small pieces of dough; roll around olives.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Blend in sugar, flour and oil.
Add flavoring, salt and soda.
To this, add pecans and raw apples. Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rosemary's rum balls
directions: Mix ingredients; form balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mushroom and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in baking dish.
Pour can of soup over potatoes.
Add water.
Spread hamburger over top of potatoes; cook until meat is done.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and syrup.
Cool.
Add peanut butter and Special K cereal.
Press into a pan.

title: better baked beans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine bacon, green pepper and onion.
Heat at High in microwave oven, 3 to 4 minutes, or until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat, covered with waxed paper, at High 3 to 4 minutes and at Medium-low 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mozzarella with tomatoes
directions: Slice Mozzarella and tomatoes.
Arrange by alternating overlapping layers on a serving platter.
Sprinkle oregano, black pepper and salt.
Drizzle olive oil.
Top with basil leaves.
Let sit 1/2 hour before serving.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon into well greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches.
Pour peaches in pan on top of butter.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, vanilla and baking powder well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a glass casserole dish. Add the tomatoes. Chop up the crackers into pieces. Mix with tomatoes. Add the sugar and spices. Put dabs of butter on top. Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, approximately 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, sugar and flour.
Then add eggs, milk, vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Prepare white cake mix as directed on package, using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in a large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from side of pan.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut centers out of bell peppers.
Place peppers in pot filled with water.
Boil until peppers are done.
Mix in bowl cooked rice, onions, salt and pepper.
Place peppers in baking pan.
Fill peppers with stuffing.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes covered.
Uncover and add cheese slice to each pepper.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix like other cookies in order given.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet, greased and floured.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Next, add wine just before serving.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: mrs. jaque casserole
directions: Cut up sausage and fry.
Remove meat and add chopped vegetables and half cook.
Add rice and pour over meat.
Add water chestnuts and vegetables.
In another bowl put 4 packages soup mix, add boiling water; mix well.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Let stand until cool.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients and chill. Before serving, add 1 liter chilled ginger ale.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tarter until soft peaks are formed.
Fold in 1 1/4 cups sifted sugar and vanilla.
Last add flour and 3/4 cup sugar, sifted together 3 times.
Pour in pan and bake at 350°.

title: round steak bake
directions: In a medium-sized casserole, place round steak which has been seasoned to taste with salt and pepper. Pour mushroom soup over steak.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat; add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt; mix well.
Process in blender until smooth.
In bowl, fold in crab meat and pimientos; mix well.
Slice bread into 1/2-inch slices and spread on crab meat mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 20 slices.

title: mom's favorite jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, jam and raisins; beat for 1 minute.
Add the nuts, jam and raisins; beat for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with favorite caramel icing.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and shred chicken; set aside.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken water.
Drain and while still very hot, add soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
Add Velveeta cheese chunks.
Blend and cheese will melt.
Pour into a Pyrex or oven dish and bake at very low temperature (250° to 300°) until ready to serve.
For a garnish, after removing from oven, sprinkle chopped red tomatoes, tiny green peppers and crushed potato chips (all optional).

title: greek lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils; drain well.
Combine with water, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and oil in a large kettle; bring to boiling.
Add tomatoes and bay leaves.
Lower heat; cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Serve with lemon juice or wine vinegar if you wish.

title: pink lady
directions: Add cranberry juice and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice; chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.

title: cabbage and ham
directions: Cook meat in water until done, then take out of water and put in cabbage.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook until tender.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter; add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Roll into small balls about the size of marbles.
Melt paraffin and semi-sweet chocolate morsels together.
Using a toothpick, dip each ball into chocolate and place on wax paper. Yields approximately 150 pieces (can be frozen).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain 2 cans Veg-All; then add all 3 cans with liquid.
Mix all together except crackers and oleo.
Cook 20 minutes; then add crushed crackers.
Drizzle oleo on top.
Bake until crackers are a little brown in a 350° oven.

title: banana split shake
directions: In a blender combine milk, coconut cream, banana, cherries and cocoa, cover and process at high. Add ice cream blend at medium speed until smooth.

title: walnut spread
directions: Blend all ingredients in processor, blender or mixer.
Serve with breadsticks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and take off the bone.
Place into ready-made pie crust.
Take chicken broth and thicken with cornstarch.
Use 2 or 3 hard-boiled eggs and cut into pieces and add.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover dish with other crust.
Cut small place in crust to allow for steam.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: southern fritters
directions: Sift flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar together. Beat eggs with milk.
Add to sifted ingredients.
Quickly stir in melted butter or margarine and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot, deep fat.
Turn once to brown all over.
These puff up into round balls.
Serve very hot with maple syrup or honey or dust with powdered sugar.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess juice.
Add carrot and green pepper.
Let stand and make the liquid solution with the remaining ingredients.
Boil these ingredients 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm, then pour salad in containers with lids.
Close tightly and place in deep freezer and use as needed.
Unused portion may be refrozen.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, stir in pecans.
Combine eggs and remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: spiced bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 12-well muffin tin with cooking spray.
Warm the molasses and honey in a small saucepan over low heat just until it begins to stream.
Remove the pan from the heat and set aside to cool.
Whisk the egg whites, yogurt and milk together in a large mixing bowl until blended.
Whisk in the molasses and honey mixture.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in the bran, flour, baking powder and spices.
Fold in the walnuts and raisins.
Turn the batter into the prepared muffin tin and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until a tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Put into baking dish sprayed with Pam and a little melted butter.
Slice pears and mix with a little sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Put into first mixture.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the celery, onion and salad dressing. Chop the eggs. Add to the bowl. Mix well. Spread the egg mixture evenly on 4 bread slices. Top with remaining slices. Cut each sandwich in half.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients as listed, into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread around, but do not stir.
Bake at 325° for at least an hour.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: cabbage or green pepper casserole
directions: Mix water and soup; set aside.
Brown meat in pan.
Add Spanish rice.
Layer cabbage or peppers in baking dish.
Spoon beef and rice mixture over.
Spread soup and water mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours and it is ready to serve.

title: graham cracker custard pie 9-inch
directions: Roll graham crackers with rolling pin.
Combine ingredients for crust.
Press 3/4 of it into pie plate.
Save remainder of crumbs to put on top of pie.
Bake crust at 400° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: miracle whip chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Let sit for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place chicken on greased grill.
Brush with 1/2 of the mixture.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes more.

title: light 'n lemony fish
directions: Arrange fish fillets in single layer in a baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except onions, and pour over fish.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, basting occasionally.
Remove fish and garnish with green onions.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix together the milk and lemonade and set aside.
Mix the Cool Whip and strawberries together and add to the first mixture. Break cake into bite-sized pieces, pour the mixture over cake and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
This serves about 20 people. Recipe can be halved for smaller groups.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Bundle 8 to 10 green beans together and wrap 1/2 slice bacon around each bundle.
Cover with sauce made of the butter or margarine, brown sugar, garlic, pepper and vinegar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and margarine.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole.
Brown bread crumbs lightly in margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 hour before cooking.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: bacon baked chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Wrap bacon around chicken breasts.
Mix soup and sour cream in separate bowl and spread over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
One half pint equals 1 cup.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients and combine with next 5 ingredients. Mix remaining ingredients and heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour over and mix with vegetable mixture.
Make a few days ahead and keep refrigerated in an airtight container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter and corn syrup over low heat until well blended.
Beat eggs for 2 minutes.
Add mixture to eggs and pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 50 minutes (or until a knife inserted into center of filling comes out clean).

title: chicken-cheese soup
directions: Boil soup starter and water 1 1/2 hours.
Add cheese and chopped chicken.
Cook until cheese melts.
This works well in crock-pot also.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs for 3 minutes with mixer on medium speed.
Add flour and vanilla and mix.
Fold in apples and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open door while cooking.

title: jiffy jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil. Stir in sausage, tomatoes, water, sugar and seasonings. Cook rice and serve with Jambalaya.

title: banana split cake
directions: Cream butter a little. Add sugar.
Beat 15 minutes until fluffy.
Spread mixture over unbaked graham cracker crust.
Lay on bananas and cover with pineapple and then whipped topping. Sprinkle with pecans and arrange cherries.
Store in icebox overnight.

title: quick n' easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy saucepan; drain.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
May be served over cooked rice or baked potato.

title: dressing
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage and crumble.
When brown, drain grease.
Add butter, onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
In a large bowl, combine dressing mix, corn, pimentos, bouillon and the pax mixture.
Mix well.
Put into crock-pot and cook for 2 hours on high.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crab cakes maryland style
directions: Pick over the crab meat, removing any cartilage or shell bits. Stir in half the breadcrumbs, mustard, mayonnaise, onion, Worcestershire, Tabasco and seasonings.
Whip egg whites until frothy and gently work into the mixture.
Use hands to shape four cakes, then coat with the remaining breadcrumbs.
Fry cakes in oil until browned on both sides.
Serve with lemon wedges or tartar sauce.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Chop all vegetables well and saute in melted margarine and flour.
Add crawfish tails and water; cook and cover 20 minutes on low fire.
Add tomato paste and seasonings and cook awhile longer. Serve over rice.

title: potato, spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach per package directions.
Stir in mashed potatoes, sour cream, salt, pepper and chives.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and sour milk (to sour the milk add lemon juice).
Add dry ingredients.
To mix use a sturdy wooden spoon.
Bake at 400°
for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9-inch round, greased pan.

title: halibut chowder
directions: In a soup kettle, saute onions and garlic in butter. Add soups, milk and cream cheese. Stir until cream cheese is melted. Bring to a boil. Stir in fish, carrots and corn. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes. Add cayenne. Makes 16 servings.

title: stewed chicken and gravy
directions: In large Dutch oven, heat small amount of cooking oil. Mix flour, salt, pepper, and garlic salt; roll chicken in flour. Place chicken in hot oil; fry on both sides. Add water to cover chicken; add onions. Boil over medium heat until chicken is done; chicken will make it's own gravy.

title: spiced vinegar
directions: Poke the bay leaves, chiles and garlic into a bottle.
Fill bottle with vinegar of your choice.
Leave in cool dark place for approximately three weeks to develop flavor.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for a week.
When ready to bake, pinch off desired amount of dough.
Let rise and bake at 450 degrees until brown.

title: jamaican jungle bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 9 ingredients. In medium bowl, mix bananas, pineapple, oil and eggs. Add all at once to oat mixture. Stir just until liquid is absorbed and mixture is thoroughly moistened. (Do not overmix.) Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Loosen edges with knife; turn bread out onto cooling rack. Cool completely. Glaze if desired. Makes 1 loaf.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash in small amount of water.
Break crackers and place in bottom of greased baking dish.
Put layer of crackers, squash and soup until dish is full.
Place small amount of liquid, where squash was cooked, in dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frantic chicken
directions: Place frozen, cut-up chicken in a large skillet.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Pour in water.
Cover.
Heat to boiling.
After a few minutes, separate chicken pieces.
Cover and reduce heat to medium heat.
Stir one or two times to get all pieces in the barbecue sauce.

title: bread sticks
directions: In the morning, grease a cookie sheet with shortening.
Place frozen bread dough on it.
Place in oven to thaw all day.
Don't turn the oven on or cover the dough with a towel.
By evening the dough will be huge.
Press down gently.
Form a rectangle out of the dough.
Don't mess with the dough a lot.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Score with a knife, pieces about 1 to 1 1/2-inches wide.
Let dough rest for 10 minutes. Cook in hot oven at 400° until browned.
Brush again with melted butter or margarine; sprinkle with cheese.
Cut and serve.

title: oatmeal judgies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter and bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oatmeal and salt and mix well.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls while hot.
Cool completely.

title: apple-chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together first 7 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
In small bowl, mix together the remaining. Gently fold dressing into chicken
when chilled and cover.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: carrot slaw
directions: Mix apples, raisins, carrots, cabbage and salt.
Mix lightly with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with nuts and lemon juice.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and eggs; add corn and mix.
Add sour cream, salt and sugar and mix.
Put in a greased casserole or bread pan and cook until done, approximately 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Stir all dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk and jam. Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish bread 3
directions: Grease muffin pans well with butter all the way to the top of each pan.
Fill batter high; sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips and bake 15 minutes.

title: low-fat red potato and broccoli salad
directions: Chop potatoes with skins on.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Drain potatoes and place in serving bowl.
Add frozen broccoli and salad dressing; stir.
Hot potatoes will make broccoli tender. Delicious hot or cold.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Using a mixer or by hand, cream and mix well the eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda; add to mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla, apples (peeled and chopped) and nuts.
Mix. Pour into greased tube or loaf pan.
Bake from 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Leave in pan while making icing.
Icing is to be put on cake while it is hot.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Blend with Crisco, egg beaten in measuring cup with cold water added to make 1 cup and vinegar.
Mix until damp (makes 5 balls).
Pie crust keeps for 2 weeks in refrigerator and longer in freezer.

title: the dutch pantry's apple fritters
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add well beaten egg and milk. Stir until batter is smooth.
Peel and core apples.
Slice thin and dip in batter.
Fry fritters in hot, deep fat on both sides until golden brown.
Sprinkle liberally with powdered sugar and serve hot.
Especially good with sausage and/or ham.

title: pineapple-orange mold
directions: Dissolve large package apricot jello in 2 cups boiling water. Drain crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges; reserve syrup.
Add syrup plus 1/2 cup water to jello mixture.
Add sour cream and beat until smooth.
Add fruit; chill until firm.

title: new year's soup
directions: Cook onion, celery and carrots in minimum water until tender. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: heavenly ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding sour cream last.
Chill overnight in the refrigerator.

title: holiday punch
directions: Add ice cubes to other ingredients.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core head of cabbage, cook in boiling water until leaves are wilted and come off easily (can also be frozen overnight).
Pare off thick part of leaves.

title: wassail
directions: Combine water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Add orange juice and cranberry juice cocktail. Bring to boil again. Remove from heat and remove spices. When ready to serve, add applejack brandy. (May use less; be your own judge.) Serve in China cups.

title: fast and fancy fish
directions: Heat margarine and oil in a large skillet over moderate heat. Dip fish in French dressing and place in skillet.
Sprinkle onion over fish.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, turn and repeat.
Serve with lemon wedges and tartar sauce.

title: sue middendorf's vegetable soup
directions: Into a large pot, put 6 quarts of water, chuck roast, any extra beef bones for flavor, old celery leaves and an onion. Cook, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, then let it cool.
Remove the meat from the broth.
Strain the broth and discard the vegetables. Put the broth in the fridge for about 2 hours.
Remove the fat when it's hardened and floats on top.
(I usually do this step overnight.)

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend on low for 30 seconds. Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. The pie makes its own crust as it bakes.
Serves 6.

title: tiny meatballs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Measure 1/2 teaspoon for each ball.
Roll and brown.
Add currant jelly and mustard.
Simmer until done.
Serves 12.

title: smoked salmon party balls
directions: Drain, bone, remove skin and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, cheese, onion, horseradish, lemon juice, salt and liquid smoke. Mix thoroughly and refrigerate for several hours.
Shape in a ball or log.
Combine pecans and parsley.
Roll ball in pecan mixture. Chill for at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: moo goo gai pan(chinese)
directions: Slice chicken and mix with salt, pepper, apple juice, cornstarch and egg white.
String snow peas.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil and add salt.
Saute mushrooms, celery, water chestnuts and snow peas for 2 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in same pan.
Fry garlic, scallions, and chicken meat for 1 minute over high heat.
Add soy sauce and sugar; mix well.
Add cooked vegetables and mix well for 1 minute.
Remove to heated plate. Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: western cheese quiche
directions: Saute Spam, onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch deep-dish pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender or with mixer until smooth.
Pour evenly into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: scrambled eggs and cheese
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients
with a fork and mix well in a bowl.
Pour into skillet over medium heat.
Mixture will begin to thicken.
Then add ham and cheese.
Stir until mixture has thickened to serving consistency.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans; place in bowl.
Add onions and green pepper. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad.
Cover and marinate for a few hours.
Drain and serve on lettuce leaves. Yield: 8 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all in blender.
Serve on salad, or use to dip chicken nuggets.

title: working woman's cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk with dry ingredients. Blend.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Top with 3 cups fresh berries, sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour 3/4 cup boiling water over berries. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: ham and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender in water with a little salt.
Do not overcook (6 to 8 minutes).
Drain well.
Saute ham in butter until lightly browned.
Mix in flour, milk, salt and soup.
Place layers of cabbage and sauce in baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Brown for 15 or 20 minutes in moderate oven.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Rinse berries and air dry on paper towel.
Place berries in a 6 cup jar; set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts.
Do not boil.
Pour hot mixture over berries; cover jar tightly and let stand at room temperature for 48 hours. Strain through several layers of cheesecloth into a jar or bottle. Seal tightly with lid.
Store in cool, dark place.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Without peeling, cut into 1/4-inch slices. Layer in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Sprinkle each layer with butter substitute, pepper, onion and flour.
Pour milk over top.
Cook in microwave or conventional oven.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except corn chips and cheese.
Spoon meat mixture over 2 cups corn chips in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook in microwave for 5 minutes.
Lightly stir halfway through cooking time, so as not to stir in corn chips.
Crush remaining corn chips.
Top casserole with crushed corn chips and cheese. Heat again to melt cheese.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Pour hot water over cocoa, then add: sugar, shortening, eggs and sour milk.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased pan and bake at 350 degrees about 15 minutes.
(Test as cake.)
Fill as a sandwich putting 2 together when cool.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt margarine.
Add pecans; set aside.
Beat eggs with sugar; add vanilla.
Mix all ingredients and pour into freezer can.
Add sweet milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Stir well, cook until slightly thick then cool.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to milk mixture.
Add beaten egg to mashed potatoes and stir into milk mixture.
Mix in flour until you have a soft dough.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Use what you feel fits your needs.

title: beef and kraut casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add tomatoes, rice, spices and water.
Put in casserole dish.
Place sauerkraut on top of beef mixture and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes a large casserole.

title: rice cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Combine milk, wine, eggs and salt.
Mix with sauteed vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with extra chopped parsley or paprika.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy chicken divan
directions: Prepare macaroni shells and cheese as directed.
On low heat, melt butter.
Blend in Miracle Whip, salt and flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: chicken with artichokes
directions: Brown chicken breasts in small amount of butter.
Sprinkle with Lawry's Italian dressing mix.
Whip cream cheese and white wine.
Pour over browned chicken.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add desired amount of artichoke hearts and continue simmering slowly for 15 more minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: peach and pineapple salad
directions: Drain and save juice from both fruits.
Combine 1/2 cup each of pineapple and peach juice.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 package vanilla instant pudding.
Mix all together.
Layer bananas, peaches and pineapple in oblong Pyrex dish.
Spread pudding mixture over fruit.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger; boil potatoes.
After potatoes are partially cooked, add mixed vegetables.
Drain off excess water.
Add hamburger and 1 large can tomato juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: savory herb-and-garlic pork chops
directions: Place the chops in the freezer until partially frozen, about 20 minutes.
Trim off all visible fat.
In a cup, combine the garlic, cumin, salt substitute, coriander, red pepper and black pepper.
Spread the mixture thickly on both sides of the chops. Place on a plate.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours.

title: meat loaf (1)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in ungreased bread pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch dish with cooking spray.
Drain spinach, squeeze liquid out.
In bowl, combine egg whites, yogurt cheese and garlic.
Whisk until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Blend in cheese and spinach. Add chestnuts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mashed bananas. Stir all dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven for metal pans.
Bake at 325° for glass pans.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans; stir in flour.
Form into small balls.
Use about 1 teaspoon for each ball.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press balls flat; top with sugar.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: beef stew
directions: Put into pan in this order.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix and let stand for 2 hours: cucumbers, onion, salt and red or green peppers.
Boil and let cool: vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over first mixture.
Let stand in fridge for 2 or 3 days.
Freeze in pint containers.
Makes 4 pints.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Trim pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute until browned. Place chops in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place mushrooms on chops.

title: not so sloppy pizza
directions: Lightly oil the pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown and drain ground beef.

In deep dish baking pan, layer on top of crust, one layer of sauce, ground beef, Cheddar cheese, ground beef, sauce, American cheese, sausage, sauce, Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni and more Mozzarella on top.
If you like peppers, you can add peppers or what you like (onion, tomato, mushrooms, etc.).
Very easy, just layer after layer of ingredients.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chip butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use Pyrex dish with lid on top (or Corning Ware).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook over low heat until thick the oleo, flour and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over potatoes and onion.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: *whipped cream frosting
directions: Make a paste of the flour and milk; cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
If lumps form, beat after removing from heat.
Cool.
Cream the butter; add the sugar and vanilla. Continue creaming.
Add paste of flour and milk and cream until fluffy.
Delicious for devil's food or coconut cakes.

title: aunt kate's applesauce cake
directions: Combine warm applesauce with soda; add shortening, sugar and dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for about one hour. You can add these ingredients for fruit cake: 1 pound walnut meats and one pound fruit cake mix.
Bake in loaf pans or large flat pan.

title: spinach omelette
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add onion and spinach (finely chopped), butter and American cheese.
Pour into a buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Bac*Os and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix
cake
and	bake
as directed.
Make holes in cake. Mix pineapple
and
sugar
together and boil 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over cake and let cool.
Mix pudding and milk together and pour over cooled cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brenda's icebox pie
directions: Bake pie shells and cool.
Saute pecans and coconut in butter and set aside.
Beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand and fold in Cool Whip.
Fill shells with filling and put in freezer for 20 minutes. Layer caramel and sauteed pecans and coconut on top of pie. Freeze overnight.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: layered salad
directions: Place in large container in layers in order listed.
Let set 24 hours or overnight.
Toss just prior to serving.

title: rumaki
directions: Wrap a slice of bacon around each water chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Place in a shallow pan.
Mix soy sauce and brown sugar.
Pour over water chestnuts and marinate for 1 hour.
Broil in oven until bacon is cooked.
You will need to turn the water chestnuts so that all sides of the bacon cook.
Serve at once.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the 1 1/2 cups sugar with shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture, alternating with sour milk.
Beat. Add vanilla and floured rhubarb, mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: famous sweet potato cobbler
directions: Mix pie crust mix according to directions on box.
Roll out dough.
Cut 1/2 of the dough into strips; put around side of Pyrex dish and across bottom of dish.
Cook potatoes until done; leave covered with juice.
Add margarine and sugar to this.
Pour this over crust in dish.
Cut remaining dough into strips; crisscross over filling.
Slice some butter on top crust; sprinkle with white and brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa (if used) together. Mix in nuts. Cream margarine until soft and smooth. Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy. Add eggs, beating well after each addition. If you use chocolate squares, blend in. Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients and blend well. Turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan and cut into squares. Dust with powdered sugar if needed.

title: egg and grits casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with onion.
Bake in a 325° oven while browning sausage on top of stove.

Sprinkle browned sausage on top of potatoes; set aside. In a large pan, empty grits and add enough water to make them creamy (not runny); bring to a boil while stirring constantly. Remove grits from heat.
Beat eggs with milk and add to grits along with the cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour egg grit mixture over potato sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until eggs set.
Serve with fruit or juice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.

title: strawberry sparkler
directions: Place sliced strawberries in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Pour strawberry puree into a pitcher.
Add strawberry juice concentrate and stir well.
Cover and chill.
tags: frozen strawberry daiquiri fruit juice concentrate

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring, water and cocoa.
Mix eggs, sugar, buttermilk, oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Add cocoa mixture, mixing well.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Pour into 2 buttered and floured 9-inch baking pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt shortening in frying pan.
Cut meat into 1-inch strips. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place meat, onion and garlic in frying pan and brown.
Add green pepper and bouillon.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat well; add rest of ingredients, folding in nuts and poppy seed last.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: crunchy spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain and finely chop water chestnuts.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill overnight to blend flavors.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, water, butter and salt in pan. Heat to boiling over medium heat.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon maple flavoring.
Serve warm.

title: creamy green bean bake
directions: Cook frozen beans according to package directions; drain.
Or drain canned beans.
In a 1-quart casserole, combine soup, sour cream and pimento.
Stir in the beans.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with French fried onions. Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: choc-o-holic cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until blended.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Grease 1 1/2-quart pan; fill 1 inch from top. Place pan in a larger pan with hot water in it.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: orange swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of the batter and set aside.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Stir gelatin (dry) and extract into the 1 1/2 cups batter.
Drop orange batter by generous tablespoonfuls randomly in 6 to 8 mounds onto batter in pan.
Cut through batter with knife in S-shaped curves in one continuous motion for swirled effect.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Place 1/3 (3) noodles over sauce.
Spread 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
First layer is sauce, second is noodles and third is cheese.
Then add the rest of the sauce on top.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Put part of cheese on top and let stand 15 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Cook chicken until lightly browned. Remove from pan.
Arrange in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix together soup, mayo and curry.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle crackers on top. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top the last five minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: elegant beef wellington
directions: Can use eye of round, not as tender, but still very good.

title: la buche de noel
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually beat in 1/4 cup of sugar and vanilla.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice crosswise squash and onions.
Sprinkle with tablespoon salt and let stand 1 hour.
Pour liquid off before combining with other ingredients.
Combine green pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed and bring to a boil.
Pack pickles into hot sterilized jar.
Cover with vinegar mixture and seal.
Chill pickles before serving.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken with carrot, onion, bay leaf and curry powder until chicken is tender.
Strain liquid and discard onion, carrot and bay leaf.
Bring broth to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until tender.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, and butter. Heat until sugar melts. Add cornstarch and water, and cook until clear. Add lemon juice and grated lemon peel. Slowly add egg yolks and milk. Heat to boil, cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, pepper, garlic salt and oregano. Add tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix macaroni with tomato sauce and ground beef mixture.
Pour into a 2-quart or larger casserole; top with pepperoni (pepperoni can be cut in quarters and mixed with meat and sauce mixture).
Sprinkle with Parmesan; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding as directed on box.
Add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix thoroughly.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer bananas, wafers and pudding.
Repeat.
Refrigerate.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat 1 cup water; pour over gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Beat cheese with milk until smooth and blended.
Gradually beat in hot gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pears and cream. Chill in a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Unmold on greens.

title: sesame chicken and celery
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Place in small bowl.
Add soy sauce and ginger; stir to coat.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Stir broth into cornstarch; set aside.
Add cooking oil; preheat wok or skillet over high heat.
Stir-fry celery and onions 2 minutes until crisp-tender.
Remove.
Add more oil if needed.
Drain chicken.
Reserve soy mixture.
Stir-fry chicken 3 minutes or until browned.
Add soy mixture to broth mixture; stir into wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover and cook 1 minute. Spoon over rice.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine juice from can of asparagus with mushroom soup and flour in casserole dish.
Spread asparagus over this.
Cut up cheese in slices and place on top.
Sprinkle with bits of butter. Put cracker crumbs on top and bake 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except French fried onions.
Bake at 350° until done.
Last 10 minutes, add the French fried onions to the top and bake.

title: layered tostada bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease oblong baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until browned. Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, beans, chilies and olives.
Mix 1 egg, baking mix, cornmeal, milk and oil until moistened; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Spread dough in dish. Spoon beef mixture over dough.
Mix sour cream, 1 egg and cheese. Spoon over beef mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes; let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with green pepper ring if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Make mashed potatoes, being sure they are very thick (instant will work).
Brown beef.
Mix cream soup, dry soup, gravy mix and water into cooked beef.
Set aside.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients real good.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Grease sides and bottom of a 10-inch deep-dish pie pan. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and pudding mix. Mix in butter, egg and milk. Beat for 2 minutes. Pour mixture into the pie pan. Arrange the peach slices on the top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth. Sift flour with soda and add alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a well oiled and floured tube pan in a 325° oven.
After the cake has baked 25 minutes, raise oven temperature to 350° and bake approximately 40 more minutes.
(Do not open oven door for 1 hour after you put the cake in oven.)

title: kentucky pudding pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add cream, melted butter, vanilla, sugar and flour mixture. Bake at moderate temperature in pie shell until firm. Add meringue, if desired.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: For Variety:
Add dill, parsley or celery seed.
Good on green salads and potato salad.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: cream salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Heat juice (1 cup) to dissolve jello.
Use juice of cherries (warmed) to dissolve Philadelphia cream cheese.
Chop cherries, celery and nuts.
Add pineapple. When jelled, fold in Cool Whip.

title: chili
directions: *More peppers (@x.3) for sweeter taste or increase meat for meatier taste.

title: party punch recipe(mai tai punch)
directions: Mix all and serve in a punch bowl with ice and fruit of your choice, such as pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges.
Vodka may be used in place of rum.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, honey, salt, vanilla and egg. Beat thoroughly.
Stir together flour and soda.
Add to first mixture and blend.
Add peanuts and mix.
Chill dough several hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Layer half of beans, soup, celery, green pepper and onion in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers and top with a layer of ripe olives, potato chips, almonds and stuffed olives.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: turkey frame soup
directions: Cook frame in 5 1/2 quarts water until meat can be removed from bones easily.
Strain.
Cook onions and tomatoes in strained broth for 1 hour.
Add beans and cook 15 minutes; add carrots and herbs.
Cook an additional 15 minutes.
Add noodles and salt; cook 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook another 3 minutes.
Turn off heat and add chopped turkey.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Add the ingredients together.
Put in cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix together.
Saute 1/4 cup chopped pecans in butter.
Put in small pans.
Top with pecans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vidalia sweet onion casserole
directions: Peel and wash onions; cut into chunks.
Boil until tender. Drain off water.
Melt stick of butter in onions and saute for 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter chewy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil (just to melt sugar and syrup). Add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix and add corn flakes.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in pan.
Stir in nuts until well coated.
Combine flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix only until blended.
Do not beat!
Add chocolate-nut mixture and again mix in carefully, not beating.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt in microwave chocolate chips, oleo and peanut butter. After melted, mix with Rice Chex.
Put in a bag with the powdered sugar.
Shake well to mix.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
May be frozen before rolling in nuts.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
