Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
Mix broccoli with soup, cheese, onion and celery.
Add rice, salt, pepper and Tabasco; mix well.
Bake in a large greased casserole dish topped with bread crumbs at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter together to boiling point in enamel saucepan.
Add flour all at once.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms into a ball (approximately 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Cool thoroughly. Add unbeaten eggs one at a time, beating to a smooth paste after each egg is added, then beat mixture until smooth and velvety.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips and cheese.
Cook at 400° for about 25 minutes.
One half cup chopped green peppers may be added to recipe for an added taste, if desired.

title: pickle slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, dry mustard (or seed), turmeric and salt and bring mixture to a boil.
Pour mixture over the cabbage, pepper and onion.
Let stand at least 12 hours.

title: honeyed chicken wings
directions: With a sharp knife, cut off the wing tips (use for other projects).
Divide the wings into two pieces.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, soy sauce, chicken broth and white wine.
Stir mixture until sugar dissolves.
Add chicken pieces to mixture; weight down with heavy plate so wings are submerged in marinade for 1 hour.
Transfer to baking dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain chicken from liquid.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Leave roast whole and place in pan.
Chop onion and green pepper and place on top of roast.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour around roast.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Remove, cool and shred meat, removing fat and bones.
Put meat back into sauce and bake for 1/2 hour more.
Great on hard rolls as sandwiches.

title: riviera strawberry salad
directions: Saute pecans in butter until slightly brown.
Toss with lettuce and strawberries.
Add dressing.

title: a bureaucrat's guide to chocolate chip cookies(total lead time: 35 minutes)
directions: Guidance:
After procurement actions, decontainerize inputs. Perform measurement tasks on a case-by-case basis.
In mixing bowl, coordinate brown sugar, sugar, butter and shortening, then, coordinate eggs and vanilla.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Cover; switch on motor for just a few seconds.
Uncover and add gradually with motor running 1 1/2 cups salad oil (less if mixture thickens quickly).
Blend only until very thick and smooth.
Refrigerate.
Makes about a pint.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; cream until light.	Add egg; beat well.
Toss flour with cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add flour and applesauce to butter mixture alternately.
Toss nuts and raisins with 2 tablespoons flour.
Fold into batter.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: biscuit-topped stroganoff
directions: Brown beef.
Combine beef, mushrooms and all but 1/2 cup onions in casserole dish.
Heat soup until bubbly in saucepan and add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over meat mixture.
Separate biscuits into 20 halves.
Place cut side down on casserole.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put on top of potatoes and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: casseroled eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into 1-inch thick slices lengthwise.
Cut the slices into strips 1-inch wide.
Cut the strips into 1-inch cubes. These should be about 6 cups.
Heat the oil in a heavy flameproof casserole and add the eggplant cubes.
Cook stirring about 2 minutes.
Add the onion, garlic, red wine vinegar, water, bay leaf, coriander, thyme and salt and pepper to taste.
Blend well.
Bring to a simmer.
Cover the casserole and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Scrape the mixture into a serving bowl and let stand until cool before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cover 11 x 14 casserole dish with cooked chicken. Cut up egg and cover chicken. Combine in bowl, cream of celery soup, cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and poultry seasoning. Mix well and pour over egg and chicken. Melt butter and combine with flour and buttermilk. Stir well and pour on top of casserole. Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Arrange wings in a shallow pan.
Combine ingredients and heat until sugar and margarine dissolves.
Cool and pour over wings. Marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours.
(For best results, marinate overnight.)
Turn once while marinating.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; turn once.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot or cold.

title: never fail cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk with margarine, sugar and salt.
When cool, add yeast.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough (approximately 6 to 8 cups).
Let rise in bowl until light.
Roll out on floured board and spread with melted margarine, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll up dough and slice. Make slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Place on greased cookie sheet or large baking pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Frost rolls while still warm with thin powdered sugar frosting or sugar glaze.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yum.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon-colored.
Stir in zucchini and flour with cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add nuts and pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and pineapple (do not drain).
Fold in bread cubes.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch square pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious when served with ham, slightly warm.

title: libby's sunny lemon cake
directions: Pour cake mix in mixing bowl.
Add lemon jello; mix.
Add oil, water and beat for 2 minutes.
Add unbeaten eggs and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at package directions. while still warm, brush on lemon glaze.

title: baked salmon and peas casserole(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix peas, salmon and Cream Sauce.
Put in baking dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven for about a half an hour.
(Bread crumbs on top must be browned.)

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift flour together with baking powder, add salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar in bowl.
Stir in egg. Add flour mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in apples.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle mixture of cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg over muffins before baking.

title: baked chicken rolls
directions: Combine chicken, 1/2 cup of cheese and salt to taste in a bowl; set aside.
Separate crescent rolls into 10 triangles; place a small amount of chicken mixture on each roll.
Roll up, as for crescents and set aside.
Stir together milk, soup and remaining 1/2 cup of cheese; spoon a small amount of soup mixture into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with rolls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Pour remaining sauce over it and bake until done.

title: pat's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Cook macaroni and chopped celery until tender and drain.
Put all ingredients together.
Warm if necessary and enjoy.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain liquid from beets.
Beets may be finely chopped in food processor or grated by hand.
Mix mayonnaise with beets.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well.
Pour in hot well greased iron skillet.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in, then sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese and peppers.
Pour in remainder of mixture and add remainder of cheese and peppers.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough water until soupy (consistency of tomato soup).
Simmer 3 hours over medium heat.

title: yum-yum balls(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and refrigerate until firm.
Store in closed container in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter. Spread half of the crumbs in a greased baking dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inches).
Arrange over crumbs in 2 layers:
oysters (drained), salt, pepper, celery, parsley, milk, liquid from oysters and remaining crumbs.
Top layer will be crumbs.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Turn oven back to 400° if it begins to brown the crumbs.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and salt gradually, blending in well.
Add vanilla.
Pour in well-greased pan and bake 70 to 75 minutes in a 300° oven, preheated.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy or 12 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies in 375° oven.
Cool 1 minute in pan, then remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions and celery in a small amount of butter.
Cook broccoli until just tender; drain.
Melt cheese.
Combine all ingredients in a saucepan or fondue pot.
Heat and serve.

title: skillet beef dinner
directions: Lightly brown beef, celery and onion in a large frying pan. Pour off drippings.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika and sprinkle over meat and vegetables.
Gradually add milk and cook slowly 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese, olives and noodles.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Beat eggs until thick and creamy; add sugar gradually, then vanilla.

Fold in all the sifted flour and baking powder, then add hot milk and melted butter. Pour into greased and floured pan. If making as layer cake, bake for 25-30 minutes, if baking in tube pan, bake for 40-45 minutes.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break egg into mixing bowl; beat slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly. Turn into a greased 6 1/2 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Pat mixture into a meat loaf shape (9 inches long by 4 inches wide).
Bake to a rich brown, 45 to 50 minutes, or until no red juice runs out when tested in center.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Use pancake turners to lift from juice and place on serving platter.

title: five spice chicken burgers
directions: Combine soy sauce, catsup, lemon juice and spices.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Combine remaining soy mixture, egg whites, bread crumbs, onions, garlic and salt.
Add ground chicken.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 (3/4-inch) patties.
Preheat broiler.
Place patties on the ungreased, unheated rack of broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Turn patties; broil 6 to 8 minutes more until no longer pink in middle.
Combine reserved soy mixture and mayo.
Serve patties in buns with lettuce leaves.
Top with seasoned mayonnaise.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the peanut butter and cream cheese.
Mix well with a mixer.
Add the milk and the confectioners sugar.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Pour this into the crust and freeze.
Keep cold.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add flour and salt and mix well.
Add milk, melted margarine and vanilla and mix well.
Mix in coconut.
Pour in 9-inch Pyrex pie plates (greased).
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.
Forms own crust.

title: tuna stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Drain and rinse.
Combine tuna, bread, onion, egg and 2 tablespoons parsley with lemon juice.
Stuff shells and place in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and 2 tablespoons parsley and pour over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pie crusts, together.
Spoon into crusts.
Chill until cold.
Keeps in refrigerator for a week.

title: old mans apple pie
directions: Fill cake pan 3/4 full of sliced and peeled apples.
Sift sugar, flour and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Put 3 slices margarine or butter on top.
Mix Bisquick and enough milk together to make stiff.
Put by tablespoon over top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven or until done.
Serve hot with milk or ice cream on top.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, egg and sour cream.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Shut oven off and let cheese cake stay in oven for 1 hour.
Do not open oven to check on it.
Remove after 1 hour and place in refrigerator.
Some fruit topping can be added at serving time.

title: ham loaf(this recipe is a holiday tradition.)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
For holiday decoration, put strips of red and green pepper on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar; put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with dry dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until browned. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with celery and Ranch dressing as dip.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Brown onion in bacon grease; add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling point and pour over beaten eggs.
Add to potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: fettuccine with vegetables
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to boil in 3 quart pot.
Add fettuccine and carrots and cook over medium heat 6 minutes.
Add broccoli and continue to cook until carrots and broccoli are tender-crisp, about 4 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with hot water and set aside.

title: cheesy wiener and pasta
directions: Cook wagon wheels as directed on package; drain.
Melt cheese and milk until creamy.
Combine cheese sauce, wagon wheels and sliced wieners until well blended.

title: pecan logs
directions: Chop 1/2 cup of nuts finely and 1/2 cup coarsely.
Mix together margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Add powdered sugar all at once.
Mix thoroughly; knead until smooth.
Knead in finely chopped nuts.
Shape mixture into two rolls 2 inches thick.
Brush with additional corn syrup and roll in coarsely chopped nuts.
Wrap; chill.
Slice into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: smart snacks with wonder dip(third place winner 1989)
directions: Clean and cut assorted vegetables into bite-sized pieces. Line a large plate with lettuce leaves.
Arrange the vegetables over the lettuce in a pretty design.
Leave a space in center of plate for dip.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water and Jell-O thoroughly.
Cool, then add pie filling and pineapple.
Let set.
Then blend together cream cheese, sour cream and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Then spread this on top of Jell-O mix.

title: rolls for 100
directions: Put water, yeast and sugar in mixing bowl and let it stand for 10 minutes.
Add melted butter and eggs and mix.
Add flour and salt.
Mix until soft dough forms.
Butter and set in warm place to rise for 30 to 45 minutes.
Punch dough down and roll out.
Put in pans and butter.
Let rise and bake at 450° until brown.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: In 4-quart bowl, layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and 1/3 pudding mix.
Repeat.
Cover with vanilla wafers or extra Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add green chilies and cheese.
Heat until melted.
Add cream and stir well.
Can be kept warm in small crock-pot.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil
potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel, cool and cube. In melted margarine saute onions and green pepper for 1 minute. Add
pimento,
seasonings
and flour.
Blend in milk, stirring until thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Stir until cheese is
melted. Spread
potato
cubes
in 3 quart flat casserole. Pour
sauce over
potatoes.
Bake
at
350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: old-time fudge
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil; set pan aside.
Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In the saucepan combine sugar, milk, chocolate and corn syrup.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugar.
This should take about 5 minutes.
Avoid splashing mixture on sides of pan.
Carefully clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until thermometer registers 234° (soft ball stage).
Mixture should boil at moderate, steady rate over entire surface.
Reaching soft ball stage should take 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Add the 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and vanilla, but do not stir.
Cool, without stirring, to lukewarm (110°).
This should take about 55 minutes. Remove the candy thermometer from the saucepan.
Beat vigorously with the wooden spoon until fudge becomes very thick and just starts to lose its gloss.
This should take about 7 minutes total. Quickly turn fudge into prepared pan.
While fudge is warm, score it into 1-inch squares.
When candy is firm, use foil to lift it out of pan, cut candy into squares.
(Or, to make molded shapes, lightly oil small individual candy molds or sheet candy molds. Working quickly, press fudge into molds, then unmold, using wooden picks to loosen corners.
Allow molded fudge to set on waxed paper until firm.)
Store tightly covered.
Makes 45 pieces or about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: impossible lasagne pie(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cover loosely and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until no longer pink.
Remove beef; drain.
Layer Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses in same pie plate.
mix cooked ground beef, 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese, 2 teaspoon of only the fresh basil and the tomato paste; spoon evenly over cheese in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix and salt with mixer 1 minute. Pour evenly over beef mixture; sprinkle with remaining fresh basil or 1/2 teaspoon dried basil.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus.
Mix drained liquid with cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mash asparagus and add to cheese and mayonnaise mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add to asparagus mixture.
Add almonds and extract.
Place in lightly oiled mold.
Chill well.

title: pizza scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Butter casserole dish. Put in potatoes and onions; top with meat.
Mix soup and milk with beater and add to casserole.
Dot with butter, cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
You may top with additional Mozzarella cheese for the last 15 minutes.

title: tabouli
directions: Note:
You should begin to soak the bulghar at least 3 hours before serving time.
It needs to thoroughly marinate and chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook celery, onion and bell pepper in margarine until tender. Add mushroom and tomato soups, chicken broth, chili powder, Tabasco sauce and salt to taste.
Mix with cooked and boned chicken and spaghetti.
Put in a 15 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Put pudding mix and milk in large saucepan; bring to a boil. Add cake mix.
Stir just to moisten.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake for 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: lamb chops
directions: Arrange chops in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over lamb. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: can't beat mom's enchiladas
directions: For a good ham or roast beef, cook in a crock-pot until done. Use broth for gravy.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Combine brown sugar and cloves; sprinkle on pan. Arrange halved pineapple slices over sugar mixture.
Combine ham and remaining ingredients except cheese; pack half of mixture over pineapple.
Sprinkle with cheese, then pack with remaining ham mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn upside down on a hot platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white bean chili
directions: Cook beans as usual, if you want.
(I use the canned).
Bring water with some celery and onion to a simmer.
Poach the chicken or turkey 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and dice.
(The celery and onion for this are not in main listed ingredients.)
Saute onion in olive oil until clear. Add garlic, chiles, herbs and spices. Saute 1 to 2 minutes. Add beans and stock, draining water if you cooked your own.
Simmer 30 minutes or so. Add meat and 1 cup cheese until cheese melts. Adjust seasonings.
Garnish with cheese, sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: parmesan baked tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in a greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine bread crumbs, Italian seasoning and garlic salt, sprinkle over tomatoes. Top with parmesan cheese, dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 325 for 15-20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pit barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan. Bring to a slow boil, stirring often. Cook about 3 hours until thick. Can be used for pork, chicken and ribs.

title: cream cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over 1 medium head of cabbage that has been chopped fine in blender.
You can also chop a carrot in for color.
Double for large cabbage.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until smooth; stir in sweetened condensed milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding. Repeat 2 to 3 times, according to the size of the dish.
Chill well.

title: apple squash
directions: Conventional Directions:
Peel and seed squash.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In medium saucepan, combine squash and cider. Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until squash is almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes or until squash and apples are very tender.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo over low heat.
Gradually add milk and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cool over cake or ice cream.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients in pan it is to be cooked in.
Mix flour and sugar well.
Stir in milk.
Stir in fruit and the juice it is canned in.
Place margarine slices all over top of mixture and bake at 450° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamy turkey-mushroom casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart round casserole.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet and crumble.
Cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms in bacon fat until tender.
Drain if necessary.
Stir in soup, sour cream, meat, salt, pepper and bacon; heat until bubbly.
Spread in casserole. Mix remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marie's lemon butter chicken
directions: Rub chicken with lemon.
Mix margarine, juice of one lemon and garlic salt.
Pour over chicken and bake.
Baste occasionally. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.
Enjoy.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together the flour and all other dry ingredients.
Cut Crisco into flour mixture.
Make a
hole in center of flour and add yeast water and buttermilk.
Mix with fork then roll out adding flour as needed.
Cut and bake or freeze.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine oil and next 7 ingredients in shallow baking dish. Add chicken, turning once to coat both sides.
Refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.
Prepare charcoal for grilling, or heat broiler.
Grill or broil chicken 4 inches from heat, turning once, 3 to 5 minutes other side or until completely cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press crescent rolls into bottom of cookie sheet, sealing seams well.
Bake as per package directions (temperature and time).
Mix with mixer softened cream cheese, dry dressing and Miracle Whip.
Spread mixture over baked rolls.
Add veggies (carrots, celery, onion, cucumber, mushrooms, broccoli, etc.). Press gently into mixture.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: strawberries in a cloud
directions: Break up cake into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat vanilla pudding with milk.
Blend in softened ice cream and pour over cake.
Combine jello with hot water.
Add thawed strawberries with juice.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash cheese casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender in small amount of water. Drain.
Add bread crumbs, cheese, egg, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons oleo.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on large cookie sheet and bake until brown.
Cool.
Mix together next 4 ingredients and spread on the cooled roll dough.
Chop vegetables (may use any fresh vegetables you wish).
Cover with wax paper and press into the cheese.

title: easy white sauce
directions: Melt butter and add flour to make a roux.
Add milk and salt. Cook on low heat, stirring until thick.
Makes 1 cup.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil together for 15 minutes; pour over browned meat.
Place in oven until meat is tender.
Cook 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: cafe chicken(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in pot and cover.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: spiced mocha coffee
directions: Combine all the ingredients; stir it to mix and transfer to an airtight container.
For each cup of coffee, use 3 tablespoons of the blend.
Makes 10 cups.
Store in cool, dry place.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream cheese and butter.
Blend in flour, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and salt. Mold 1 tablespoon dough around each olive, covering olive completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Walnuts, pecans or cocktail frankfurters may be substituted for olives.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes, drain, pull off of stems.
Mix cream cheese and splenda and beat with fork or mixer.
Add vanilla.
If too stiff you may add a little milk.
Then fold grapes around mixture until coated.
Nuts may be added if you desire.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, soup, cheese, milk and mushrooms, if desired.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Refrigerate and let set until partially thick.
Beat evaporated milk until fluffy and add sugar and lemon juice to jello mixture.
Fold in milk.
Pour vanilla wafer crumbs in 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: roasted chicken(very easy)
directions: Cut bouillon cubes into quarters.
Cut lemons in quarters if big or poke holes with fork in smaller ones. Dry chicken.
Salt and pepper the inside. Rub outside with butter, then salt and pepper. Stuff chicken with lemons and bouillon cubes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients over low heat until smooth.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips or Hershey bars over low heat.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: "mom" allan's minute fudge frosting
directions: Bring slowly to rolling boil, stirring and boil vigorously for 3 minutes and take off heat.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla until thick enough to spread.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: * You may use more curry powder if you like.
It tastes different if left out.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Boil 1 cup of water with cranberry sauce in a pan, then pour into jello and cut up carrots, celery and mix with pineapple. Pour boiled mixture into cut up ingredients.
Add another cup of cold water and stir until mixed.
Chill until firm.

title: mom's sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until firm and add 1/2 cup of sugar slowly.
Beat egg yolks with water until foamy and add remainder of sugar.
Continue beating until yolk mixture is thickened.
Add flour, salt and baking powder (sifted together) to yolk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg white and put into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese; then fold in marshmallow cream. Use as a dip for apples, pears, strawberries or bananas.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In a blender mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a quart jar.
Store in refrigerator.
It will thicken as it sets.
Makes 3 cups.
One and one-eighth cups equal a 15 ounce can.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Grate the sharp cheese.
Chop onion and green pepper into small pieces.
Drain pimento.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into two 4 to 5-inch balls.
Coat with chopped walnuts.
Best if served with Town House or Ritz crackers.

title: green chili squares
directions: Grease 7 1/2 x 11 dish. Mix all ingredients together and pour into dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then lower heat to 250° for 30 minutes longer. Cut into squares and serve warm. Yield: 35 squares.

title: crab meat in shell soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion, green pepper and celery in butter, but not brown.
Add broth, tomatoes, shells, salt, pepper and parsley. Bring to a boil. Cook 30 minutes.
Add crab meat. Cook 5 minutes longer.

title: dump cake
directions: Place the crushed pineapple with juice in the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place the can of pie filling in the pan next. Distribute the yellow cake mix evenly over the pie filling, followed by the pecans.
Pour the melted butter over the entire combination.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse and drain. Coat with salad oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Mix remaining marinade ingredients and pour over noodles.
Let marinate in refrigerator two days, stirring occasionally.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: quick dip
directions: Mix the Good Seasons, mayonnaise and sour cream (or low-fat yogurt).
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings overnight in sauce made from mixture of all ingredients.
Bake in foil lined pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Serve on cantaloupe circle.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes, checking after 7 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: brownie carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed 2 minutes. Stir in pecans. Grease and flour pan.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Check with toothpick at center. Cool on wire rack. Cut into squares. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cabbage bean soup
directions: Brown beef or turkey.
Drain well.
Put into large pot or slow cooker.
Add tomatoes, onion, pepper, cabbage and seasonings.
Add water to cover vegetables.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Add kidney beans, undrained

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Starting with lettuce, layer everything in dish.
If dish is deep enough, you can repeat layers if you make the layers thin enough.
This is better after it sits awhile in refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water and cook until done.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium low heat until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed and heated through stirring occasionally.
Freezes well.

title: boston brown bread(a quick version that doesn't have to be steamed!)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour and soda together; stir in dry crumbs.
Cut in shortening with fork or pastry blender until mixture looks like meal.
Mix remaining ingredients in and stir until well blended.
Pour into 2 well-greased No. 303 cans (use multiple soup cans for smaller loaves), filling each a little over half full.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: cream corn
directions: Mix all together and put in large roaster.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every half hour.
Cool completely and put in freezer Ziploc bags.

title: portuguese sweet rice
directions: Boil 1 cup of rice until almost cooked; drain the water and replace with fresh water, just enough to cover rice (no more). Over a very low flame, add 1 can evaporated milk slowly.
In a bowl, mix 5 eggs and 1 cup sugar.
When rice is cooked, stir in egg mixture, stirring constantly, until completely blended.
Cook for just another minute.
Do not dry rice.
Raisins may be added. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Break up cake in baking dish.
Cover with strawberries, then cover with strawberry glaze.
Cover with banana pudding (prepared as directed) and Cool Whip and garnish with coconut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and add flour and rest of ingredients. Stir in zucchini, nuts and raisins. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit bowl
directions: In a bowl, dump everything together, then slice bananas.
Let sit for 30 minutes. Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: original barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan over high heat and whisk until smooth. Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until thick. Cool, then store in a covered container in the refrigerator overnight. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lulu's bourbon balls
directions: Mix all together; roll in balls and in powdered sugar.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs well; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend with eggs.
Add drained crushed pineapple.
Cut bread into 1 to 2-inch cubes.
Stir into mixture.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grate American cheese; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour 1/2 of the batter into 10 x 10-inch pan.
Spread cheese over batter.
Cover with remainder of batter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: old-fashioned apple brown betty
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine bread cubes, melted butter, spices, salt and brown sugar and toss lightly together. Arrange bread mixture in alternate layers with diced apples in 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish. Bake 50 minutes or until apples are tender and top is browned. Serve warm. Add whipped topping and sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Marinate sauerkraut and mayonnaise 30 minutes. Arrange pieces of turkey, Swiss cheese and corned beef on 6 buttered slices of rye bread.
Spread 1/3 marinated sauerkraut on each slice of bread.
Top with bread slice; cut into halves.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine broccoli and water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover; microwave 7 to 9 minutes on High.
Drain and arrange in an 8 x 8-inch microwave dish.
Microwave in small dish for 1 to 2 minutes on High the onions and butter.
Place the cream cheese in the onion and butter mixture.
Microwave 30 to 60 seconds.
Stir into this the soup, lemon peel, salt and pepper.
Pour this sauce over the broccoli; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave for 5 to 7 minutes on Full power.
Rotate dish halfway through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip picnic bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugars together until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts. Spread dough into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
While still warm, sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar and cut into bars.

title: cocktail cracker surprise
directions: Mix dry ingredients and pour over box of Ritz Bits in large bowl.
Stir well.
Allow to set for an hour or two.
Can be used immediately or will keep well in the freezer for later use.
Used as a munchie.

title: tuna health salad
directions: Combine all except optional ingredients into a bowl and mix gently.
Serve on a bed of lettuce and garnish with onion and tomatoes.
Serve chilled.
Serves 4.

title: paulette's burritos
directions: Lay out approximately 8 burrito shells.
Layer each shell with the ingredients in their listed order.
Fold shells over, put on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: shrimp in cream cheese sauce
directions: In large saucepan over medium-low heat, melt cream cheese with undiluted soup, stirring frequently, until melted and smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook slowly until heated through.
Serve with rice or toast points.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. place in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish with cover. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: dressing for the elite
directions: Simmer first 8 ingredients together. Cool for 10 minutes. Blend in the catsup, olive oil, capers and juice and the Worcestershire sauce.
Add garlic. Cool dressing at room temperature for 1 hour.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Shake well before using.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.

title: hot chocolate espresso
directions: In a large cup or mug, mix the coffee and sugar, if desired. In a small saucepan over low heat, warm the cream. Add the cocoa and mix well. Add the cream mixture to the coffee and top with a dollop of whipped cream and the grated chocolate. Serve with a cinnamon stick.

title: spinach squares
directions: Wash, cook and drain spinach well.
Beat eggs well; add butter, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir in grated cheese and cooked spinach.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; level off.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: pistachio ice cream cake
directions: Crush crackers very fine.
Mix nuts with cracker crumbs; add melted margarine and mix.
(Save some cracker mixture for topping.)
Press crumbs into bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan to form crust.
Mix pudding with milk and softened ice cream.
After this is thoroughly mixed, spread in pan over cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip over top of pudding mix and top with remaining crumbs. Keep in freezer until 20 minutes before serving.

title: quiche
directions: Cook pie crust 5 minutes before filling.
Mix and pour ingredients into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, then put on baking sheet to cook for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Drop by tablespoons.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until edge is brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place a layer of pork chops in a deep bottom baking dish or pan, then a layer of potatoes and a layer of onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat layer, then pour mushroom soup over all the ingredients; use 1 can of water.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and Clear Jell.
Dissolve strawberry jello in hot water.
Mix jello and hot water into sugar and instant Clear Jell. Add 2 1/2 cups strawberries and stir until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Put on desired topping.
Makes 1 pie.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Saute green onions in small amount of butter.
Add crabmeat and cream cheese, softened.
Remove from heat and add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Delicious in chafing dish, kept hot/warm, with Triscuits.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, cook chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Blend cake mix (dry mix) thoroughly into hot pudding by hand or electric mixer (1 to 2 minutes).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream, if desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well
after
each
addition.
Add
flour,
reserving
2 tablespoons.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add flavorings and reserved flour
with baking soda.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan
at
325° (preheated oven) for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Start testing
for
doneness
at
1 hour and 10 minutes, using toothpick in center of cake.

title: crock-pot no-bean chili
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil and saute beef.
Saute onions, green peppers, jalapeno peppers and chili powder; add seasonings and stir.
Remove from pan and add beer; pour in crock-pot with meat. Cover and cook 6 to 7 hours on medium-low.
Skim fat, thicken by adding cornmeal.
Cook additional 15 minutes uncovered.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add spaghetti sauce, sugar, salt, chili powder and mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix sour cream, onions and softened cream cheese.
In casserole, layer spaghetti, meat mixture and sour cream mixture, ending with spaghetti.
Sprinkle cheese generously on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown together first 5 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients; simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Mix together Ricotta cheese and eggs. Have ready the Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook lasagna in 3 quarts boiling water, plus 3 teaspoons oil and 3 teaspoons salt.
Add 1 to 2 strips at a time.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until pliable; drain, then layer as follows:
First lasagna, meat sauce, Ricotta/eggs, Mozzarella and Parmesan; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together Crisco or oil, sugar and food color.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the cocoa, salt, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and flour.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice cake with Red Velvet Cake Icing.

title: raspberry mousse(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Force raspberries through a sieve, and cook until berry mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: lefse
directions: *Ten pounds potatoes makes 4 batches of about 12 to 15 per batch.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Add vanilla and water.
Bring to a boil.
Serve over biscuits, bread, pancakes, etc.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.

title: corn rice casserole
directions: Put chopped onion and green pepper in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Cover with rice and corn.
Cover with 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water.
Place meat in a layer on top of sauce. Salt and pepper and add Worcestershire sauce, then cover with second can of sauce.
Cut bacon into strips and cover top.
Cook covered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and pour off grease; cook 15 more minutes.

title: italian market salad
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Cut
shrimp
in
half.
Melt butter and blend in flour. Add seasonings.
Add cream gradually and cook until thick and smooth. Stir
constantly.
Beat
egg yolks; stir a little hot sauce
into egg
yolks.
Add
egg
mixture into remaining hot sauce.
Add shrimp
and heat through.
Do not boil or it will curdle.
Remove from heat and stir in sherry.
Serve over rice or puff pastry shells.

title: corny dogs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip boiled wieners until thoroughly covered. Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: crepes
directions: Measure dry ingredients into a bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Lightly butter an 8-inch skillet. Heat over medium heat until bubbly.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into skillet; immediately rotate pan until batter covers bottom.
Cook until lightly brown; turn and brown on other side.
While warm, spread with desired filling.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 12 crepes.

title: rice-vegetable meat casserole(from 1975 edition)
directions: Brown the hamburger in the margarine, breaking it up with a fork to have it in crumbles.

Then in a greased 2-quart casserole or baking dish, arrange in layers, first the meat layer, then a layer of each of the vegetables, one on top of the other, in the order listed, ending with the hot water.
Cover and bake in a slow oven at 325° for approximately 2 hours.
Add more water if needed during the cooking period.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Thaw spinach souffle.
Remove stems and clean mushrooms.
Mix souffle with Jack cheese and green onions and sausage.
Stuff the mushrooms with spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ginger ale sherbet punch
directions: Combine 1 quart of ginger ale and 1 pint sherbet, beating well before adding any more.
Continue adding in these proportions as needed.
For extra body to the punch, add vanilla ice cream every so often.
Yields 50 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Work together brown sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly. Spread apples in greased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Combine water, lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg; pour over apples.
Spread crumbly mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: moonshine beans
directions: Fry onion in bacon grease; drain.
Mix all ingredients well. Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: parmesan chicken and crispy potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges (24 wedges total). On an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, arrange wedges in a single layer, skin side down.
In a small bowl, combine the first 2 tablespoons oil, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, paprika, garlic salt, 1/2 teaspoon thyme and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Brush Parmesan mixture onto wedges; set aside.

title: fried corn
directions: Scrape corn; fry bacon.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Stir corn into drippings.
Add 1 1/4 cups water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
In small bowl stir together cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir into corn, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces and brown in a large Dutch oven.
Drain grease.
Add broth and seasonings.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Add celery, onion and green pepper. Simmer about 30 minutes or until tender. Add tomatoes and zucchini. Simmer until they are tender.
Serve hot!
Leftovers freeze very well.
Crusty French bread or garlic bread and a tossed salad go very well!

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove bones from salmon and shred finely.
Add egg, chopped pepper, onion and parsley.
Shape into patties and roll into cracker crumbs.
Fry in greased, preheated frypan; turn when brown.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Refrigerate overnight; at least 8 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press crust into desired pan; chill. In small bowl mix jello and hot water.
Chill, do not let set.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Roll dough out about 1/2-inch thick and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in small bowl, beating with mixer.
Beat in Cheddar cheese and next 8 ingredients until creamy.
Stir in parsley and pimento.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours, until firm enough to handle.
Shape into ball and coat evenly with nuts.

title: lo-cal company salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss together.
Let stand 1 hour or more before serving.
Very low in calories.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: potato-bean soup
directions: In large saucepot, cook celery, carrots and garlic in margarine over medium heat for 4 minutes.
Carefully stir in broth, potatoes and dill.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
With the back of a spoon, lightly mash 1/2 of potatoes in the broth.
Add beans to potato mixture.

title: grape jelly
directions: Wash grapes, pull from stem, crush thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup water.
When grapes get hot, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Wet bag (pillow case) and wring dry.
Pour grapes into bag and squeeze out juice.
Allow 5 cups juice and Sure-Jell to come to a hard boil.
Add sugar.
When mixture comes to a boil that cannot be stirred down, start timing and boil 2 minutes.
Skim.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal while hot.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine in a crock pot and cook on slow for 4 to 5 hours, until veggies are soft.
Don't cook too long or cheese will turn brown or burn.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except steaks.
Score steaks and marinate for at least 4 hours.
Grill at least 4 minutes on each side.
The steak should be carved on the diagonal in thin slices. It may be served with small rolls or threaded on skewers and warmed just enough to heat through.

title: matt's mexican surprise
directions: Brown meat with salt and pepper; drain on paper towels.
Put in mixing bowl; add soups, milk and cheese.
Fold in crushed chips and jalapeno.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be served as an entree or a dip with additional chips.

title: mock chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine meats, herbs and spices, egg and breadcrumbs in a large bowl.
Mix well with hands.
Form into 6 patties.
Roll each patty in cornflake crumbs, coating well. Fry in oil until golden brown.
Remove to a shallow baking pan and bake 20 minutes or until cooked through.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place two inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 56 cookies.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, pepper and onion.
In saucepan, mix egg, vinegar and sugar.
Cook until it looks like scrambled eggs.
Mix together; chill.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Whisk together all ingredients except shrimp.
Pour mixture over shrimp; cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Place shrimp and liquid in shallow pan and bake at 500° until shrimp are pink. Do not overbake, this does not take very long to cook.
Serve over linguine or rice.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter; add to sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together and cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: sherbet tea punch
directions: Pour hot tea over sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves; add juices, chill.
Then pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Spoon on sherbet.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiris
directions: Blend on high speed of blender.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Make popcorn.
Spray inside of grocery bag with cooking spray.
Place popcorn in bag.

title: dolly parton super soup(lo-cal)
directions: Cut and chop all vegetables into small chunks.
Boil in water* with bouillon cubes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until nearly done.
Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange coconut supreme
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 3 large layers.

title: christmas coffee cake(may prepare ahead.  freezes well.  serves 8 to 10.)
directions: This is my traditional Christmas coffee cake which I bake and give to special friends for their Christmas breakfast.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix in the milk, egg and melted shortening.
Spoon into shallow pan (8-inch square). Bake for 20 minutes, until lightly browned and all edges let go. Set oven at 425°.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Mix braunschweiger with mixer until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pan (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square 9 x 9 x 3/4 inch pan or a 10 inch skillet.
Mix undrained pineapple, butter, brown sugar, and spread in bottom of pan or skillet.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt into a bowl.
Add shortening, egg, milk, and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Bake 45-50 minutes.

title: beef and sausage hors d'oeuvre
directions: You will need aluminum foil and a cookie sheet.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except lemon-lime drink.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 3 hours before serving.
Add drink just before serving.
Stir.
Serves 30.

title: seven-layer casserole
directions: In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer rice, ham, onion and broccoli.

title: *mystery pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and egg.
Put in a 9-inch square pan and cover with fruit cocktail, including juice. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on the top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite topping.
Serves 9.

title: eggnog rice pudding
directions: Heat eggnog over low heat.
Combine cornstarch and milk.
Pour into eggnog.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins.
Stir in salt and rum extract.
Fold in rice.
Pour into dish.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually until creamed well, then add eggs.
At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour and lemon juice.
Add melted butter and sour cream.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around the edges.
Turn off oven and let cake sit in oven for 2 hours.
Remove after 2 hours and cool completely.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop and mix the above with the cooked macaroni or spaghetti. Stir in half a bottle of Supreme salad seasoning.
It is better if you let chill one whole day.

title: banana split
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and pat into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat the eggs, margarine and powdered sugar for at least
minutes	and spread over graham cracker mixture. Cover this with sliced bananas, then pineapple (well drained). Top
with Cool
Whip.
Sprinkle
with
nuts	and
refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef and onion.
Add cream cheese, soup, milk and catsup.
Stir and mix well.
Pour into a quart or larger casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and add the biscuits.
Bake additional 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves around 4.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken along with celery, onion, carrots and 3 tablespoons butter.
After chicken is done, debone and add back to broth and vegetables.
Add 3 packages of chicken gravy mix and noodles.
Stir and simmer until noodles are done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon parsley meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix together beef, parsley, bread crumbs, onion, milk, salt, pepper, thyme and lemon peel.
Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch meat balls and brown on all sides in hot oil.
Add 1 cup water; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl pudding
directions: Place chunks of cake in fruit bowl.
Add some pudding, pineapple, bananas or whatever fruit you desire in layers.
Add whipped topping and then start over again until you have as much as you need.
At the top, spread topping and nuts.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Stir well.
Let stand until yeast makes small bubbles.
Add eggs and flour; mix to smooth soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise until at least double in bulk.
Divide dough in six.
Roll each 6th to 9-inch circle.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut circle in 12 or 16 wedge-shaped pieces.
Roll each wedge.
Starting at wide end, roll to point.
Arrange in greased baking pan.
Cover and rise until very light.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer wafers and bananas until bowl is full.
Mix salt, sugar, milk, flour and eggs in saucepan.
Cook on low until thick, stirring continuously.
When mixture begins to thicken, take off the stove and add vanilla and margarine.
Pour mixture over layers in bowl.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: chocolate cake dessert
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions, using a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven and poke holes all over cake top with a toothpick.
Pour condensed milk and caramel topping over cake.
Cool completely.
Spread whipped topping over top of cake and sprinkle with grated chocolate. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Microwave on High 5 minutes; stir well.
Microwave 8 to 12 minutes more or until mixture reaches hard ball stage. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites, beating at high speed with mixer.
Add vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes more or until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Fold in chopped nuts. Quickly drop teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter and add stems, green pepper and onion and cook until soft.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings to taste and fill center of washed mushroom caps.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in baking dish; place mushrooms in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Put under broiler for 2 minutes, until brown.

title: amazing rice
directions: Mix rice and soups in a casserole dish that has a tight lid. Put the margarine in the middle and do not stir.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Fluff with a fork.
Excellent for potluck!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together plus 1/4 cup corn juice (leave out the crackers).
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour in dish and spread crackers on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Slice meat, cutting across the grain, into thin diagonal strips (3 x 1-inch).
In a small bowl, combine bouillon, soy sauce and m.s.g.; set aside.
Heat 2 to 3 tablespoons of the oil in a heavy skillet.
Add half of the meat; brown, turning frequently.
Add half the bouillon and soy mixture, then push meat to one side of the pan.
Add half of all the vegetables except spinach, keeping each vegetable separated.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, turning often.
Add half the spinach and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Serve immediately with rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook celery and butter until clear; add soups, cheese, broccoli, onions, salt and pepper.
Put rice in a buttered casserole dish.
Pour mixture over rice.
Cook in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch into a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in the syrup, water, margarine and salt.
Heat to a hard boil; stir constantly.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Just cool to handle and pull to stretch, then shape while warm.
Then wrap and serve.

title: tater tot casserole(club member: terah smith)
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion; drain. Mix soup, cheese and other ingredients. Top with Tater Tots and put margarine on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350° until Tater Tots are done.

title: spinach mushroom casserole
directions: Arrange layers of spinach, noodles and 3/4 cup cheese in 1 1/2-quart baking dish or casserole.
Blend soup with milk and nutmeg; pour over top.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Melt butter in medium sized saucepan.
Stir in coconut; remove from heat.
Press mixture against sides and bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix by directions on box; cool.
Mix pudding as directed but use 1 cup less milk.
In punch bowl crumble half of cake.
Put 1/2 of pudding on cake.
Drain pineapple.
Put 1 can on pudding.
Put 1 can cherry pie filling on pineapple, then 1/2 of Cool Whip on cherry pie filling and sprinkle 1/2 of nuts on Cool Whip.
Repeat!

title: snack-time
directions: Mix together.
Spread on bite-size bread slice.
Bake until golden on top.
Serve hot.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour peaches and juice over mixture.
Bake at 350° until sides of cake pull from sides of pan.

title: green bean chile
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer 2 hours.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, brown beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, breaking up into 3/4-inch crumbles.
Remove beef; pour off drippings.
In the same skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Stir-fry bell pepper and pea pods 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add rice, soy sauce and sesame oil; mix well. Return beef; heat through, about 5 minutes.
Stir in green onions. Garnish as desired.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; form into balls.
Put into greased pan.
Pour tomato soup, mushroom soup and water over meatballs.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix bananas and pineapple. Add lemon juice and sugar, then add rest of ingredients. Pour into a buttered Pyrex dish.
Freeze and when ready to serve, cut into squares.

title: chili in 30 minutes or less
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground round, onion and garlic. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients all except beans. Simmer, covered, 30 to 45 minutes, until flavors are blended. Stir in beans and heat through.

title: lime frost
directions: Empty frozen concentrate into chilled blender.
Add ice, 1 cup at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stop blender several times and push ice down with rubber scraper.
Add few drops green food coloring, if desired.

title: dill carrot sticks
directions: Peel
carrots.	 Cut
into 3-inch lengths
and	quarter lengthwise into sticks.
Cook in boiling salted water about 10 minutes, just until crispy tender.	Drain.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar; cook to make syrup for 3 minutes.
Let cool and add orange juice, pineapple juice, lemon and bananas. Freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Slush with a potato masher.
Add 7-Up or other beverage just before serving. Makes 5 quarts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl and then add the remaining.
Combine all these ingredients and stir by hand.
Pour the mixture into a greased Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Lay
pork
chops in pan.
Cover with onions, garlic and soy sauce.
Bake
at 375° to 400° until almost done.
Add 1/2 cup water to mushroom soup.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake until tender. Soup will make a gravy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook in water until tender.
Drain well.
Mix potatoes, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Place in a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover top with marshmallows; then brown sugar and last add pecans.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 325° oven or until marshmallows are melted and light brown.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Melt caramels with milk in saucepan.
Cool slightly.

Combine remaining ingredients, except for chocolate chips and walnuts. Press half of the oatmeal mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle crust with chocolate chips and walnuts. Drizzle caramel mixture over all. Cover with remaining oatmeal crumbs.
Press slightly. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
In saucepan, melt butter, cocoa and Coke.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry mixture.
Add marshmallows, buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Remove from bone in bite size pieces. Place in 10 x 14-inch pan that is 3-inches deep.
On top of chicken, place pimentos, onions, parsley and chopped eggs.
Use flour and enough sweet milk to make thickening for the broth. Pour over chicken and pour crust over all.

title: zucchini vichyssoise
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add zucchini, chicken broth, basil, nutmeg and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Puree soup. Return to pan and add milk.
Serve cold or hot.
Makes 6 entrees or 10 to 12 small courses.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Brown and cook ground meat on medium fire.
The last 8 minutes of cooking ground meat, add onions and cook until tender.
(Drain all oil off of meat.)
Put small amount of oil in an iron skillet and brown just a little corn meal in bottom.

title: unknown chicken
directions: Dust chicken in mixture of 1 tablespoon flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet and brown chicken.
Put chicken in baking dish.
Saute mushrooms.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons flour in with mushrooms.
Add wine and soup, stirring until thick.
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Dice ham, tomato and jalapeno and mix with 1 package of cream cheese.
Spread onto flour tortillas and roll; place into refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour, then cut and serve.

title: marinated mushrooms 1
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms in a large glass bowl.
Using a whisk, blend well.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Pour juice over last. Cook on low at least 12 hours.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Spread butter evenly on bread slices, taking to edges of bread. Sprinkle with garlic powder and cut into cubes. Bake at 350° until crispy. Store in airtight bags. Will keep for several days.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Simmer bacon and onions until brown. Drain grease. Add beans, mustard, ketchup and brown sugar. Mix well. Pour into casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat gelatin, pineapple and sugar in saucepan until dissolved. Cool, then add buttermilk and nondairy topping.
Fold in thoroughly and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour meat loaves
directions: In food processor or meat grinder, grind meats together.
Then add all remaining ingredients (except the last 3 which will be used for sauce to baste while cooking).
After ingredients are mixed real well, make into small loaf-like balls and put into baking pan (cover).

title: roy's western peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips for 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Pour peanut butter chips on top of melted chocolate chips.
Melt 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir together chocolate chips and peanut butter chips. Stir in Spanish peanuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and let stand at room temperature.
Makes 60.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, herbs, salsa picante and garlic salt.
Chill.
Serve as a dip for chips or crisp vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: wheat germ muffin
directions: Combine biscuit mix, wheat germ and sugar.
In another bowl, combine egg, water, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until dry mixture is moistened.
Don't overbeat.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 6 muffins.
Easy to double.

title: frosted orange refresher
directions: Combine the juice concentrate, sugar, dry milk, vanilla and cold water in a blender and process at high speed.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time.
Blend until slushy.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.
A very refreshing cool drink on a hot day and evening.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put chunks and juice into 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together and spread over pineapple.
Crush the Ritz crackers; spread over top.
Pour melted oleo over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir until mixed. Add coconut and raisins.
Add pie crust; mix.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender (drain).
Place in a casserole. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spoon over carrots.
Mix crumbs and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350° or until hot.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onion, green pepper and celery. Fry over low heat, stirring frequently, until onion is limp.

Add broth, parsley, potatoes, tomatoes, carrots, cabbage, beans, garlic, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, oregano and basil; cover and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Taste for seasoning.
Add water to make up to 3 quarts. Add macaroni and cook about 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: mom's tater tot dish(microwave)
directions: Lightly spread ground beef in bottom of 10 x 8-inch microwavable dish.
Sprinkle soup mix on top.
Mask with soup. Top with Tater Tots.
Microwave 20 to 22 minutes on High or until soup is bubbly and ground beef is firm.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shredded cabbage toss
directions: Combine prepared vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss lightly. Garnish with green pepper rings.
Serves 4.

title: butter-pecan turtle bars
directions: For crust, in electric mixer, mix the first 3 ingredients at medium speed for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pat firmly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over unbaked crust.

title: slow-cooked pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 3 x 1-inch strips. Brown
in oil in skillet. Transfer to slow cooker.

title: mother's sand tarts
directions: Combine sugar and butter and mix well.
Add eggs; keep white of one.
Cream; beat well.
Add flour and other ingredients.
Blend. Roll dough thin.
Use cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar, peanuts and cinnamon.
Bake at 350°.

title: easy broccoli cheese soup
directions: Mix ingredients together. Heat and serve.

title: roasted asparagus with thyme
directions: Place asparagus on baking pan (with sides) lined with heavy-duty foil.
Drizzle with oil and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered at 425 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Serves:

title: little deb's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixer bowl.
Spoon out onto pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: western egg sandwich
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp and crumble.
Heat salsa in pan on medium heat.
Beat eggs and add with bacon to salsa.
Cook, stirring often, until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put the eggs on your favorite bread and enjoy a great sandwich.

title: jubilee salad
directions: Drain liquid from can of dark sweet cherries with water to make 2 cups.
Heat to boil with jelly; add to raspberry Jell-O. Add frozen raspberries, wine and/or 7-Up and lemon juice.
Add cherries and chill until partly congealed.
Mold and chill.
Serve on greens.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Sift flour and confectioners sugar together 3 times.
Beat together egg whites, cream of tartar and salt with a wire whisk or electric mixer until foamy.
Add 1 cup of sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and almond flavorings.
Sift flour mixture gradually over the top; fold in gently, just until flour mixture disappears.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cold water and cornstarch together in saucepan.
Add sugar.
Cook until boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the box of jello.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Add sliced strawberries.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tangy big fruit salad
directions: Put bananas on bottom, then peaches.
On top, put the Tang and sour cream.

title: minted breakfast drink(a marvelous, healthy, refreshing drink to help you wake up.)
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Drink at once.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Boil altogether for two hours.
Take beef and grind.
Add enough good brown flour to thicken.

title: mom's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and margarine.
Mix crumbled wafers with milk. Combine with other ingredients.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: sloppy joes skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat and add Sloppy Joes mix, beans, tomatoes and brown sugar.
Stir, cover and simmer. Serve over rice.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix well in pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken breast salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts in Pam and cut into cubes.
Marinate in Catalina dressing.
Toss with other ingredients which have been cut up; use amounts as desired.
Lace with toasted almonds.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and egg.
Add sugar, cornstarch, seasoned salt, dry mustard and minced onion.
Stir in milk and melted butter. Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Add all ingredients, except egg whites.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in buttered mold in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put the rice in the water in the top of a double boiler and cook until water is gone. Scald milk and evaporated milk together. Both milks should equal 2 cups; add

water to make it. Add scalded milks to rice and place over boiling water in the other half of the double boiler. Stir and cover; cook for 30 minutes, until boiling. Add vanilla extract. Make sure to keep the water level in the bottom pan high enough. Beat eggs and 1/2 cup sugar together (eggs at room temperature). Slowly add egg mixture to rice, stirring constantly until it thickens. Pour into pan. Let cool; sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: sugar-free jam
directions: Mix pears and fructose.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add Jell-O and Sure-Jell.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in small jars and seal.

title: graham bread
directions: Mix
dry ingredients in bowl, then add wet ingredients. Pour or spoon into greased bread tin and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Add topping.

title: microwave enchilada casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add onion and green pepper.
Microwave, uncovered, until meat is firm (5 to 6 minutes).
Stir to break up meat.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, enchilada sauce and beans (with liquid).
Cover and microwave to boiling (3 to 4 1/2 minutes).
Spoon 2 cups meat sauce into oblong baking dish (7 1/2 x 12-inches).
Place 1/4 cup remaining meat sauce in center of each tortilla.
Fold sides over filling, overlapping edges.
Place tortillas, seam sides down, in baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over tortillas.
Cover loosely and microwave until hot, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving juices.
Measure 1 1/2 cup of juice and set aside.
Combine dry pudding mix and Tang in a bowl.
Add the reserved 1 1/2 cup juice.
Do not beat.
Add pineapple, oranges and bananas and mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add peanut better and milk.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in cool whip.
Turn into prepared crust.
Chill 5 - 6 hours.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots and set aside.
Gently cook onion
in
the butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard
and
then milk.
Cook, stirring, until smooth. Add pepper and celery salt.
In a buttered, 2 quart casserole, arrange a layer of carrots and then a layer of cheese.
Repeat until both are used.
Pour on sauce and top with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes or until golden.
Serves 8 people.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Cut caramel candy cubes into fourths; dredge in flour, adding apples, caramel topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Top with pecan pieces.
Bake on a preheated cookie sheet (to collect spillage) in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: peach crumb cake
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients into mixing bowl at once and mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix the last 3 ingredients into crumbs; sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add to other ingredients.
Top with part of crumbs, cheese and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add water.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Add to broccoli.
Then add eggs.
Mix gently until well blended.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: potted beef
directions: Trim fat from the tips and cut into cubes.
Place all of the ingredients into a saucepan and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: raised drop donuts
directions: Soak warm water and yeast until dissolved.
