Combine sugar, shortening, eggs, salt, nutmeg, 2 cups sifted flour and warm milk. Beat for 2 minutes. Add yeast mixture and beat.
Add 2 cups more of sifted flour and beat 2 more minutes.
Cover and place in a warm spot for 45 minutes. Drop in hot oil. Take 1/2 teaspoon dough and push off spoon with another spoon.
Roll in sugar or glaze.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Place bite-size chicken over broccoli.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and chicken broth; pour over chicken breasts and broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Crush 1 small package Ritz crackers and melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Mix and pour over casserole.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: grandma carr's catsup
directions: Cook all together 2 hours.
Then run through sieve.
Recook until right thickness.
Can and seal while hot.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients well, then add coconut and marshmallows.
Mix, then add sour cream.
Mix well, then let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: hamburger quick
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain.
Blend next 4 ingredients; stir in meat, onion and cheese.
Pour into pie shell or baking dish lined with sliced potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: baked beans, pineapple and frankfurter casserole
directions: Mix all together, except frankfurters; put buttered franks (whole or halves) scattered over the top.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon together in bag and use to coat biscuit pieces.
Generously grease (Pam) a tube pan such as a Bundt pan (do not use an angel food pan with a removable bottom).
Layer the biscuit pieces in the pan. Put chopped nuts in between layers, if desired.
Cook oleo and brown sugar together, boiling for one minute.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand for about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Using fingers, pluck bites from cake, monkey see, monkey do!
Enjoy.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in shredded zucchini; set mixture aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Reserve 1/4 cup flour mixture and toss with raisins and pecans.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions, cooking for only 5 minutes.
Drain broccoli; put into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with onion rings.
Bake an additional 8 to 10 minutes longer or until onion rings are crisp and golden brown.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Heat milk and chicken broth together.
Blend oleo and flour together; add seasonings.
Blend into hot liquids and cook until smooth, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Into a greased baking dish, layer the turkey, or chicken if preferred, a generous layer of creamed gravy and a layer of bread crumbs.
Repeat until baking dish is full.
Dot with oleo or butter.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes servings for 4 to 6 people.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a tube pan for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Be sure to grease the pan before you put the batter in.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl, excluding 1/4 cup grated Velveeta cheese, mix well.

title: skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Add other ingredients except rice. Boil until pepper is tender.
Add rice and simmer until rice is done.

title: mushroom stuffing
directions: Saute green onions, celery and ham in butter until vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add bread crumbs.
Add the beef bouillon if moisture is needed before adding to a roast.
This is really good with a tenderloin or good prime roast.
I like to put roast and stuffing in a browning bag.
It really absorbs and holds the juices.

title: monster toast
directions: Pour milk into 3 or 4 separate cups.
Add different colors of food coloring to each glass of milk.
Use a paint brush to paint a monster (or whatever) on the front of a piece of bread.
Toast; butter lightly.
Eat.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in crock-pot that has been greased with shortening (or Pam spray).
Put sliced cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low heat.

title: buckeyes -- buckeyes -- buckeyes!
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Beat and beat and beat and beat!
Roll in balls and refrigerate for 2 hours; dip in chips, melted with paraffin.
Use toothpicks to dip and store in refrigerator!

title: grandma's strawberry meringue torte
directions: Beat butter and 1/2 cup sugar with electric mixer until creamy.
Add yolks, one at a time.
Add milk.
Beat until smooth. Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Continue beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Beat (room temperature) egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add remainder of sugar (3/4 cup) and cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks are formed.
Spread meringue over batter evenly.

title: garlic chicken breasts and rice
directions: Wash chicken breasts and place into a baking dish.
Sprinkle well with garlic salt and add pepper to taste.
Mix together melted butter, 1 cup water, rice and soup.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour or until chicken is done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Serve plain or with fruit toppings.

title: japanese pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, eggs, coconut and raisins.
Mix well, then add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: one dish mexican dinner
directions: Place 6 tortillas in bottom of long pan.
Brown meat and add salt and chili powder.
Drain.
Spread over tortillas.
Spread beans over meat.
Slice cheese thin and spread over beans.
Cover with 6 tortillas.
Blend soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes well.
Pour over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add liquids and mix well. Gently fold in blueberries.
Makes 18 muffins.
Bake 16 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream together at high speed in your mixer the cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
When smooth and creamy, gradually add 1 1/2 cups flour.

When it gets too thick for the mixer blades, continue kneading by hand until you can form the mixture into a roll about 1-inch in diameter. Wrap the roll in plastic wrap or wax paper and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Slice into thin layers and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
You can freeze before or after baking.

title: quick raisin squares
directions: Combine raisins, sugar and water; put on stove and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a 2-quart casserole dish. Steam the cauliflower and broccoli until just tender.
Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan.
Saute scallions until soft. Remove scallions with a slotted spoon.
Set aside.
Stir the flour into the oil in the saucepan and cook until mixture bubbles.
Add milk and stir constantly to keep lumps from forming.
Add cheese, mushrooms, parsley and dill.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Add salmon, steamed cauliflower and broccoli with sauteed scallions to cheese mixture.
Transfer to casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes or until the cheese has formed a light brown crust.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; cook rice.
Mix together.
Put into casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Combine with both soups.
Pour over broccoli and rice.
Top with sliced cheese.
Put cracker crumbs on top of cheese.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix other ingredients.
(Stir until smooth and add all ingredients.)
Then add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
While spinach is draining, saute onion in butter.
Add spinach, salt, pepper and garlic.
Spoon half of spinach mixture into 9-inch pan.
Spread Cheddar cheese and half of Mozzarella cheese and cover with remaining spinach.
Spoon egg evenly over top.
Sprinkle rest of Mozzarella cheese and then bread crumbs.
Bake until spinach is piping hot and cheeses have melted, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter; mix together with graham cracker crumbs.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick of butter, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Place bananas on top, followed by pineapple.
Add Cool Whip on top of fruit.
Pour chocolate syrup on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cover with remaining batter and cinnamon mixture.
Cut to marbleize with knife.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool. Do not invert pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend soup, cheese, beaten egg, milk and margarine.
Pour over broccoli in baking dish.
Melt butter; pour over top of bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over broccoli mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all other ingredients in 10-inch baking dish, covering the cooked broccoli.
Cover with Ritz crackers (crumbled).
Sprinkle cheese over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then vanilla, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in oatmeal.
Mix dry ingredients, then add to moist ingredients.
Chill dough.
Preheat oven to 375°. Form dough into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in powdered sugar. Press down. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: microwave cheese fudge
directions: Microwave butter and cheese until melted.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Add to cheese and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Press into a buttered dish and chill.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Add 1 cup cooked rice to stretch recipe.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cheese, shrimp and onion.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: spicy pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Add other ingredients, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir frequently.
Put in clean, hot jars.
Process 20 minutes for pints and 25 minutes for quarts in boiling water.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Boil slowly until clear.
Add 3 tablespoons strawberry jello and mix well.
Pour glaze over fruit in pie shell.
Chill several hours to set.
Top each slice with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: zwieback
directions: Melt butter in warm milk.
Add sugar, salt and yeast, dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add flour to make a soft dough. Knead until dough is velvety and elastic.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and let rise again until double.
Form dough into small balls, placing one on top of another.
Let raise until almost double and bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: apricot unbeatables
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and egg whites.
Add nuts and apricots; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 325°.
Cool on rack. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles about halfway through meat process in 2-quarts salted, boiling water until al dente.
Drain and toss with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Keep warm over hot water.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
Heat skillet, then add 2 tablespoons margarine.
When melted, add meat and brown quickly.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes or until onion is clear.
Remove meat mixture from pan.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine to pan drippings. Blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add 1 tablespoon tomato paste.
Stir in beef broth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Return browned meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in sour cream and white wine (if desired).
Cook slowly until heated through.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: bing salad
directions: Drain off juices and crush up cheese.
Heat until cheese dissolves.
Pour over Jell-O and add Cokes slowly.
Add other ingredients after draining juices from cherries and pineapple. Add water to juices to measure 2 cups.
Chill the Cokes.
So good!

title: mexican french bread
directions: Cut French bread in the middle and remove almost all of the underside, trying to leave only the crust.
Spread butter on the underside of the bread.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon on the bread.
Place in the oven on a cookie sheet and bake at 400°
until the butter is boiling. Wait a while before you eat them or you'll burn yourself.

title: tallarena
directions: Brown beef in pan with onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Add noodles and tomatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cheese on top and simmer about 10 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice into bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Heat 3 soups, margarine and 1 cup water on stove top.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: diabetics strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells.
Place in refrigerator for an hour before serving.

title: nutty fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler; add milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-buttered 12 x 8-inch glass dish.
Let set overnight or until it is dry on top.
Cut into squares.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except nuts, with electric mixer. Sprinkle nuts on bottom of greased and floured Bundt pan.
Pour the rest of the ingredients over nuts.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: waldorf salad (jello)
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 2 1/2 cups. Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened. If necessary remove any unmelted ice. Fold in fruits and celery. Spoon into individual dishes or a bowl. Chill until set, at least 1 hour. Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Boil cranberries and water until berries pop.
Add Jell-O and sugar until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into bowl or mold.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add all other ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of sauce into a casserole and layer with tortilla and cheese. Repeat and end with cheese on top.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Mix together in order listed the egg, sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Then mix together apples, chopped nuts and sherry.
Blend both mixtures together and pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add ingredients and mix well.
(You do not need to cook broccoli first.)
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for approximately 50 minutes.

title: barbecued venison(moose, elk, etc.)
directions: Put all of the ingredients (except lemon or lime slices) in a blender to liquify, if family is finniky about "chunks." Otherwise, just mix the sauce ingredients together.
Place steaks in water with the vinegar or lemon juice, to draw out as much of the remaining blood as possible.
Leave for half an hour, then drain and pat dry.
Place in a roasting pan and cover with the sauce.
Place the lemon or lime slices all around the meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour longer.

title: too easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan and salt and pepper.
Mix all the ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: s'more brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
In medium bowl, beat butter and sugar until blended.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, graham cracker crumbs and baking powder; beat until well blended.
Press half of dough in pan; spread with Marshmallow Creme.
Arrange 4 1/2 chocolate bars over dough.
Carefully press remaining flour mixture over chocolate bars, covering completely.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
In small microwave-safe bowl, place remaining 1/2 chocolate bar that is broken in pieces and shortening.
Microwave at High power for 15 to 30 seconds or just until chocolate is melted when stirred. Drizzle over top and cut into bars.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Press evenly into dish. Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Blend in ice cream.
Fold in 2 crushed candy bars. Spoon into prepared dish. Freeze for 30 minutes. Top with whipped cream and remaining crushed candy bar. Store
in refrigerator.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together sugars, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Sift
together dry ingredients.
Add the 2 together; stir until smooth.
Blend
in
coconut.
Drop
by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake
at
for
to 15 minutes. Makes 3 or 4 dozen soft cookies.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and put over chicken, pork chops, venison steaks the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: two minute hawaiian pie
directions: Blend above ingredients and pour into a baked shell.
Top with whipped cream topping and sprinkle with coconut or red or green cherries or nuts (or all of the above).

title: new potatoes with herbs
directions: Wash potatoes leaving skin and if desired boil just until they start to become tender.
Drain and saute in skillet with butter.
You can slice the potatoes instead of leaving whole.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Place on a baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot pie
directions: Sprinkle sugar, lemon juice and flour over apricot halves (do not need to be peeled).
Toss gently.
Place in two crust pie shell.
Dot with butter before putting on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes or until crust is brown and fruit is bubbly.

title: orange meringue rice pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine milk and rice.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and cook over low heat, about 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in 1 cup of hot rice mixture into beaten egg yolk.
Return all to saucepan. Stir in orange marmalade to taste, vanilla and salt.
Pour rice mixture into 8 x 6 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir rice mixture well.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a large bowl, put salmon.
If desired, remove any large pieces of skin.
With fork, flake salmon and crush the small bones.
Add remaining ingredients except oil.
Mix well with clean hands and form into patties about 1/2-inch thick.
Heat large frying pan on a griddle with enough oil in it to grease bottom of pan.
Fry salmon patties (4 to 5 at a time) over medium heat on one side until browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Remove to heated platter.
Add a little more oil and cook remaining patties. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato wedges
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine the butter, orange juice, salt and cinnamon. Drizzle over sweet potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until tender. Yield: 10 servings (8 cups).

title: mexican meat dip
directions: Layer bottom of baking dish with refried beans.
Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add taco seasoning, then the chopped green chillies; add jar picante sauce.
Pour over refried beans.
Top with shredded cheeses and bake until cheeses have melted.
Cool a little bit and dip tortilla chips or any chip in mix.
Enjoy.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put the apple pie filling into a large baking dish.
In a bowl, mix the cake mix with 3/4 cup butter and pecans.
This will be a crumbly texture.
Sprinkle on top of the pie filling and bake at 350° as directed for cake.

title: nibbles
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereals, mixed nuts and pretzels in bite size pieces.
In a 2 cup glass measure, combine remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until butter melts.
Mix well; pour over dry ingredients.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring to mix ingredients every 2 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: steak marinade
directions: Stir together.
Use to marinate steak.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch morsels
directions: Melt butterscotch chips with peanut butter over low heat, stirring until well blended. Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated. Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Keep in refrigerator.

title: spinach bread appetizer
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Scoop out the center of the bread and fill with the mixture. Arrange bread cubes around loaf to dip in.

title: hearty chili
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain off fat.
Combine tomatoes and bean liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup. Add tomatoes, kidney beans, liquid mixture, chili powder and macaroni to skillet.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Add water as necessary.
Serves 4.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with a nonstick spray.
Pour cake mix (dry) and spread it around.
Pour hot water over dry cake mix. Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
The cake will rise to the top and the bottom will be like pudding.
If you want the cake on the bottom and pudding on top, use cold water.

title: oriental noodle and chicken stir-fry
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil.
Stir in noodles and cook 3 or 4 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir once.
Drain.
Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch cubes.
Preheat browning skillet on high for 5 minutes or until very hot.
Quickly add oil and chicken cubes.
Stir until lightly browned, about 45 seconds.
Add garlic, onion and mushrooms and cook 3 or 4 minutes until chicken is tender.
Combine soy sauce, honey, sherry, curry powder and sesame oil.
Combine noodles and chicken mixture and saute together, tossing to coat.
Garnish with green onions and sesame seed.
Serve warm.

title: polish dumplings
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in mixer on medium speed and then finish by hand.
Add flour, working with wooden spoon and then with hands, until about 4 1/2 cups are added.
Break off apple-size (small) chunks of dough.
Flour hands and start rolling dough between hands to form a rope, then cut off pieces with a paring knife about 1-inch long, dropping them onto a floured cookie sheet.
Then flour hands and proceed to roll each of these pieces between palms of hands to look like "little fingers." Place these on a floured cookie sheet.
Continue with the rest of the dough.

title: potato kugeli
directions: Cut bacon and fry.
Set aside.
Grate potatoes and onion.
Add eggs, bacon and drippings, milk and seasonings.
Pour in greased baking dish, about 9 x 12 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
To prepare crust:
In a medium saucepan, place 1/4 cup sugar and the butter.
Heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Stir in crumbs and press mixture gently over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time, and vanilla, until well blended.
Spoon blueberry filling evenly over crust.
Carefully pour cream cheese mixture over blueberries.
Bake just until set, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Chill about 2 hours.
Makes 24 squares.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients and cook in crock-pot, 8 to 10 hours until meat shreds easily.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: room fragrance
directions: Mix into a smooth dough.
Make into 7 small patties.
Wrap in lace and tie with ribbon.
Attach a paper clip and hang anywhere.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Simmer beef and onion on top of stove for a short while. Shred cabbage in bottom of a baking dish.
Drain grease from beef and onion.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not overcook.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions (use minimum recommended time for boiling); drain noodles and place in large bowl with butter, cream and cheese.
Add salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
Stir ingredients together.
Serve immediately.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dressing over top and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Batter will be stiff; add nuts.
Stir and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan or three (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° approximately 40 minutes according to pan size used.
May be iced if desired.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and add sugar and butter.
Pour into large, oblong dish.
Beat together until thick the pudding and milk, then add the softened ice cream and beat until mixed together well.
Set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Then top with Cool Whip.
Put grated Heath bar on top.
Let set 3 to 4 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate (best if made the day before serving). Can be used with round rye bread loaf with center cut out and dip placed in center.

title: pink cloud jello dessert
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Refrigerate and let set.
When jello is set, remove from fridge and beat with mixer until frothy, then add Cool Whip and bananas and whip just until mixed.
Spoon into individual sherbet dishes and return to fridge to set.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Beat eggs whites until very stiff.
Add sugar.
Spread over layer No. 2.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown in oven.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Grease 9-inch tube pan.
Combine pecans, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
In large bowl beat butter and 1 cup sugar.
When creamy beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, 1/4 at a time.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Arrange apple slices on this and sprinkle with 1/2 pecan mixture.
Add remaining batter, then pecan mixture.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 325°.

title: rotini and cheese
directions: Cook rotini; drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix in cheese soup and 1/2 can milk.
Add peas and chopped Spam.
Mix. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with margarine and pour remaining 1/2 can of milk over top.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain and rinse in cold water. Drain.
Microwave peas and carrots as directed.
In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Toss, chill and serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and liquid ingredients separately. Combine dry ingredients and liquid mixtures.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick spray.
Lightly saute onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Add a little margarine, if needed.
Remove from pan when lightly browned.

title: manna
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, beat well.
Add honey, salt and vanilla.
Combine baking powder and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by half teaspoons onto buttered cookie sheet.
Top with seeds, 3 each.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans, mustard, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Brown beef; stir into bean mixture.
Add green pepper, if desired.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter together.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
In a separate bowl, sift together, soda, flour and salt.
Add half at a time to creamed mixture until all mixed in.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Blend all together; pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes more.

title: german meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brush pork chops with mustard and roll in flour.
Fry into golden brown.
Place in baking pan.
Mix 2 cans chicken noodle soup and 1/2 can water and pour over pork chops.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until tender.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat eggs until light and add to mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Pour into an approximate 10 x 13-inch size pan and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: captain broccoli
directions: Layer cooked broccoli in bottom of casserole. Daub with butter. Add cut up squares of cheese (2 in section).
Cover with the soup, milk, tuna, more cheese squares and the onion rings. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes with cover on.

title: pork chop one dish meal
directions: Place chops on bottom of large casserole dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Place potatoes or sprinkle rice over chops.
Pour soup/water mixture over all ingredients.
Cover and cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill about 1 hour. Serve as dessert or salad on crisp salad greens. Makes 6 cups or 12 servings.

title: indian chicken breasts
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Puree until smooth.
Place chicken in shallow dish.
Pour marinade over and turn to coat.
Cover and let stand at least 15 minutes. Preheat grill or large cast-iron skillet over medium heat. Spray cooking surface. Cook 4 minutes per side.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well and chill.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried octopus(octopus fritti)
directions: Clean
octopus
by
soaking
in salt water and pounding octopus against side of bowl.
This helps remove any sand that may be
trapped
in
suction cups.
Cut off head and only use tentacles.
Wash,
rinse
and drain again.
Cut with scissors, keeping
tentacles together.
Drain octopus in colander and place
flour
in
bowl with pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet and dip
octopus
in flour and then into oil.
Fry on medium-high heat, cooking about 8 minutes on each side.
Brown well, but
be careful not to burn.
To serve, place on warm platter with
lemon wedges,
if desired.
Keep warm in oven until all frying is complete.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and the onion is tender.
Drain.
Put into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish and stir in apples, kraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.
Very good.

title: party squash
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash.
Add other ingredients except butter and crumbs.
Place in 2-quart casserole; top with crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff over rice
directions: Tenderize steak.
Cut into 1/2 x 4-inch strips.
Roll in seasoned flour.
Put oil in skillet and brown garlic in oil.
Add steak strips and brown, turning each strip over.
Slice onion thin and separate rings and layer over steak strips.
Add water and simmer, covered, until tender.
Add a little more water if needed. Add mushrooms and simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice that
chicken bouillon cubes have been added to cooking water. Some cooks add 1/2 cup white wine to the steak simmering water.

title: lemon chiffon cake(angel food mix)
directions: Move bottom rack in oven to lowest position.
Heat to 350°. Beat egg whites as directed, using only 1 cup water.
Mix four packets with remaining ingredients.
Fold the two together.
Bake in angel food cake pan 40 to 50 minutes.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Put spaghetti sauce and cheese on top of English muffin.
Cook in a 350° oven until cheese goes blub, blub, blub.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil
and
flavoring
until
thick
and creamy.
Stir in drained
zucchini
and
all other ingredients. If desired, add 1/3 cup sesame seed or 1 cup walnuts or pecans. Divide into 2 greased and floured
loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add hot water and oats; let stand until cool.
Cream sugars and Crisco; add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Add oats.
Bake in baking loaf pan at 350° for 35 minutes or in glass dish at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Put on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: finnish fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add the sugar, continuing to beat. Mixture should be beaten well and light in color.
Add the dry ingredients, taking care not to overbeat.
Pour into greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then slice layers in half.
Alternate layers of cake, fruit and whipping cream, as you would for a torte.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: f f fudge
directions: Stir together for 15 minutes: make sure it is for the full time.
Pour into buttered jelly roll pan.
Refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes before cutting.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Cook soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add pepperoni slices.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: Cut meat in bite size cubes.
Peel onion and cut in rings. Peel and cut carrot in slices.
Wash bell pepper, remove inside kernels and cut in strips.
Leave canned tomatoes in the juice, but cut them in pieces.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add onions and meat and brown for 5 minutes while stirring.
Add carrots and bell pepper, stewed tomatoes and spices.
Mix well and stir in 1/2-quart water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in half and half right before serving.

title: creamy green onion spread
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in onions; chill.
Serve with favorite crackers.
Yields 1 cup.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Cut into lengthwise strips 1/4 to 3/8-inch wide.
Arrange potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole in three layers, topping each layer with dash of pepper and 1/3 each of the salt, parsley, onion and cheese.
Dot with butter and pour half and half over potatoes.
Cover and cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes longer.

title: crab and cream cheese appetizer
directions: Form cream cheese in a ball with one flat side.
Thaw crab and put it over the cream cheese ball on plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over this.
(Add some horseradish to sauce if you like more zest.) Serve with crackers.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed about 2 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating at
medium
speed
for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at
a
time.
Combine
flour, baking soda and cocoa; add to creamed
mixture
alternately
with sour cream.
Mix at lower speed just until blended.
Stir in vanilla.

title: fudge filled bars
directions: In a bowl, combine the oats, flour and brown sugar. Add butter and mix until crumbly. Stir in the pecans. Set aside 1 1/2 c. for topping. Press remaining crumb mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. In a saucepan, combine milk, chocolate chips and shortening; cook and stir over low heat until chips are melted. Spread over crust; sprinkle with the reserved crumb mixture. Top with M&M's. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Dip eggplant in the beaten eggs, then cover in bread crumbs. Brown both sides of eggplant. Alternate layers of eggplant/Mozzarella cheese/marinara in casserole dish. Final layer top with marinara and Mozzarella cheese (ok to add little water to jar of remaining marinara, do not make it watery, but just enough to cover). Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or so.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and beat on low speed 1 minute. Beat on medium speed 1 minute. Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: potato casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked potatoes and mix.
Put in buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put together and blend in blender.

title: crispy baked onion rings
directions: Cut each onion into 4 thick slices.
Separate into rings, reserving small rings for other uses.
Set aside.

title: communion bread
directions: My sweet potato, do you carrot all for me?
You are the apple of my eye with your radish hair and turnip nose.

title: pastrami skillet dinner
directions: Cut turkey pastrami into 1/4-inch slices; set aside.
Combine chicken broth, flour and mustard in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat stirring until thickened.
Add potatoes and cabbage. Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add turkey pastrami and onion.
Cook for 10 more minutes.

title: noodles and sauerkraut
directions: Remove rind from salt pork; dice, fry until crisp, remove and cool.
Add mushrooms, onions, oleo and soup mix to grease; simmer 10 minutes.
Wash sauerkraut and add to mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add cooked shells and salt pork; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lida crawford's chicken pie
directions: For pastry, break 1 egg in cup; finish filling with milk.
Add baking powder, shortening and flour.
I sift flour in medium sized bowl; make hole and work up with hands.
Knead until stiff enough to roll for dumplings.
Roll thin and divide in 3 pieces.
Cut in strips, put layer of chicken first, then layer of dumplings, another of chicken, then dumplings and more chicken.
Cut eggs in rounds and place on top, then top crust.
Pour enough boiling broth over pie to keep moist.
Place stick of butter on top.
Bake until begins to brown.
Add Pet milk; put back in oven to finish.
Makes a huge pie.

title: melba rounds
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Mix oleo, caraway seed, bacon and cheese.
Spread on Melba rounds.
Broil until brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Empty jello into large glass bowl.
Pour in boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Let stand until slightly thickened.
Pour the thawed berries into the jello and beat two minutes with eggbeater.
Put into refrigerator to set completely. Serve and enjoy.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk until mixture will slide off a large spoon.
Stir in pepper and onion.
Drop by teaspoon into moderately hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
(Good cooked in oil in which fish has been fried if oil is not burned or too brown.)

title: baked rice
directions: Heat the oils over medium high heat.
Add the rice, five-spice powder and ginger and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add the broth, sherry and red pepper.
Cover the pan and cook over warm heat for 30 minutes or until done.
Add more broth as needed to make sure rice is soft.

title: mustard pickle
directions: Pour
boiling	water
over
cabbage,
green
tomatoes, peppers and
corn with salt.
Boil 1/2 hour.
Drain off water. Cook cauliflower, celery
and lima beans separately until done with no salt.
Drain off
all
water.
Mix	this
in
with the other vegetables, then put in a large kettle, 2 quarts vinegar and 5 pounds sugar.
Let this
get real hot, then pour in your paste and stir.

title: toasted mushroom rolls(servings: 10)
directions: Finely chop mushrooms.
Saute for 5 minutes in butter.
Blend in flour, salt, garlic and marjoram.
Stir in cream.
Cook until thick.
Add chives and lemon juice.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix 1/2 of water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch and rest of water and sugar thoroughly mixed to the first half and boil until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add salt, lemon juice and coloring.
Mix well.
Pour this mixture over whole strawberries in pastry baked pie shell.

title: barbecue bacon chestnuts
directions: Wrap each chestnut with 1/2 slice bacon and secure with toothpick.
If necessary, cut chestnuts in half to make the same amount of chestnuts and bacon strips.
Arrange bacon wrapped chestnuts in shallow baking pan.
Broil until crispy, about 5 minutes on each side.
Drain well.
Blend chili sauce, brown sugar and mustard; pour over bacon wrapped chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar-apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined eggs, milk and oleo. Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove from pan and cool before slicing.

title: toasted pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 2 tablespoons butter in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Blend well. Add vanilla and 2/3 cup pecans.
Turn into 2 (9-inch) round cake pans, well-greased and floured on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Pecan Frosting.

title: chocolate cherry cheesecake
directions: In large bowl, combine chocolate wafer crumbs and butter.
Pat firmly into a 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and 2 1/2-inches up sides.
Chill.

title: roast beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Chill 1 hour or until firm.
Shape.
Roll in pecans.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add flour gradually.
Mix with beaters.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out cookies with a floured round cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place warm cookies in container to keep soft.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into tube pan (or angel food cake pan).
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon over batter. Pour in remainder of batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add eggs and remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour in the tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Cook and drain mixed vegetables.
Rinse and drain kidney beans.
Mix all vegetables and macaroni together.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Pour over vegetables while still hot.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight or longer.
